WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:34.757 --> 00:01:41.094
Subtitles ripped by cjdijk.

3
00:01:43.354 --> 00:01:44.314
Hmmm...

4
00:01:45.565 --> 00:01:47.650
What a lovely dream.

5
00:01:49.027 --> 00:01:50.028
Hello?

6
00:01:50.779 --> 00:01:52.530
What is this place?

7
00:01:53.948 --> 00:01:56.034
Hey. who's that? Ow!

8
00:02:12.258 --> 00:02:13.134
Hello.

9
00:02:15.095 --> 00:02:17.931
Be patient. little buzzer.
it's still too early.

10
00:02:18.139 --> 00:02:20.391
But I have to tell you
about my dream.

11
00:02:20.600 --> 00:02:23.269
There was this big.
bright round yellow thing.

12
00:02:23.478 --> 00:02:25.146
And all this blue.

13
00:02:25.355 --> 00:02:27.649
- Bees don't dream.
- Why?

14
00:02:27.857 --> 00:02:29.067
Well...

15
00:02:29.901 --> 00:02:31.361
They just don't.

16
00:02:31.569 --> 00:02:34.322
Now rest. Bees never
hatch until the sun rises

17
00:02:34.531 --> 00:02:35.740
over the daffodils.

18
00:02:35.949 --> 00:02:37.617
Why can't I just
do what I want?

19
00:02:37.826 --> 00:02:39.702
A bee do what she wants?

20
00:02:39.911 --> 00:02:41.037
Oh...

21
00:02:43.123 --> 00:02:44.207
Patience. little bee.

22
00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:48.545
There's plenty of time
for learning later.

23
00:02:48.753 --> 00:02:51.422
- What's a bee?
- A bee is a good little girl

24
00:02:51.631 --> 00:02:53.133
who does what she's told.

25
00:02:53.341 --> 00:02:55.468
<i>Rock-a-bye bay-bee.</i>

26
00:02:55.677 --> 00:02:57.637
<i>'m her wax nest.</i>

27
00:02:57.846 --> 00:03:00.390
<i>When nursie says.</i>

28
00:03:00.598 --> 00:03:02.142
<i>bay-bee will rest.</i>

29
00:03:02.350 --> 00:03:03.852
<i>Good baby.</i>

30
00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:05.645
go to sleep...

31
00:03:05.854 --> 00:03:07.564
That's enough. little one.

32
00:03:07.772 --> 00:03:09.190
Hey!

33
00:03:09.399 --> 00:03:10.650
<i>In you go-</i>

34
00:03:11.943 --> 00:03:15.363
A bee who does what she wants?
Ridiculous!

35
00:03:17.282 --> 00:03:19.701
- What are we making?
- How...?

36
00:03:19.909 --> 00:03:20.994
Now listen here!

37
00:03:21.202 --> 00:03:22.328
We're not going
to tell you again.

38
00:03:22.537 --> 00:03:24.831
<i>Go. Back. In.</i>

39
00:03:28.376 --> 00:03:29.460
There...

40
00:03:29.669 --> 00:03:31.379
Everything is fine.

41
00:03:33.965 --> 00:03:36.759
- What a sweet little bee.
- Sweet?

42
00:03:36.968 --> 00:03:38.511
Now. what was her name?

43
00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:41.681
Baby-Bee 396.

44
00:03:41.890 --> 00:03:43.433
396.

45
00:03:44.309 --> 00:03:45.018
Maya.

46
00:03:46.019 --> 00:03:48.146
She's where she belongs now.

47
00:04:02.702 --> 00:04:04.120
Wow!

48
00:04:08.958 --> 00:04:11.377
Hello. busy bees!

49
00:04:15.715 --> 00:04:17.133
What is this?

50
00:04:19.677 --> 00:04:22.597
- This is fun.
- Bees don't have fun.

51
00:04:22.805 --> 00:04:23.765
Get off.

52
00:04:27.143 --> 00:04:29.062
Help! I can't see!

53
00:04:32.232 --> 00:04:34.525
- Excuse me!
- Hey. what?!

54
00:04:37.237 --> 00:04:39.614
I can't see.
I can't see.

55
00:04:39.822 --> 00:04:41.199
I don't want to see!

56
00:04:42.367 --> 00:04:44.827
Listen to that buzz.
Your Majesty.

57
00:04:45.036 --> 00:04:47.497
That's the sound
of good little bees

58
00:04:47.705 --> 00:04:50.250
keeping this
great hive efficient.

59
00:04:55.880 --> 00:04:57.799
This was so fun!
Did you see?

60
00:04:58.007 --> 00:05:01.094
I was all the way up there.
then I was like. “Bzzz!”

61
00:05:01.302 --> 00:05:02.553
Miss Big Bee.

62
00:05:02.762 --> 00:05:04.013
you've got something
on your head.

63
00:05:04.222 --> 00:05:05.765
- Is it heavy?
- Silence!

64
00:05:05.974 --> 00:05:09.477
Clean this up! This is a hive.
not a filthy hornet's nest.

65
00:05:09.686 --> 00:05:13.398
Pull your stinger in. Buzzlina.
She's just a baby.

66
00:05:13.606 --> 00:05:15.483
I'm sure it was an accident.

67
00:05:15.692 --> 00:05:17.151
If we allow bees to run amuck

68
00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:19.529
like this the hive
will fall into chaos.

69
00:05:19.737 --> 00:05:22.240
She is right.
Every bee in this hive

70
00:05:22.448 --> 00:05:25.159
- has a role to play.
- What's my role?

71
00:05:25.368 --> 00:05:28.204
Patience. little one.
You'll find your place.

72
00:05:28.413 --> 00:05:30.999
You just need to learn how
everything works first.

73
00:05:31.207 --> 00:05:34.627
But she broke the rules.
She must be punished!

74
00:05:34.836 --> 00:05:38.089
See that she gets to
school safely. Buzzlina.

75
00:05:38.298 --> 00:05:40.842
Of course.
Your Majesty.

76
00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:43.219
"Every bee has
a role to play..."

77
00:05:45.013 --> 00:05:47.432
We must do something
about the Queen. Crawley.

78
00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:49.934
She's not fit to rule this hive.

79
00:05:50.143 --> 00:05:52.395
Right. you little menace...

80
00:06:04.532 --> 00:06:05.700
Hey!

81
00:06:09.537 --> 00:06:11.581
- Halt.
- Halt!

82
00:06:11.789 --> 00:06:15.960
- What kind of bee are you?
- A marchy bee. like you. silly.

83
00:06:16.169 --> 00:06:19.422
I hardly think so.
Bees don't behave like that.

84
00:06:19.630 --> 00:06:21.716
Fall in. soldier!

85
00:06:21.924 --> 00:06:22.800
Shoo.

86
00:06:37.315 --> 00:06:38.733
Attention!

87
00:06:44.322 --> 00:06:45.990
Attention!

88
00:07:07.970 --> 00:07:09.722
Wow.

89
00:07:27.782 --> 00:07:30.993
Whoa. Beautiful.

90
00:07:52.140 --> 00:07:55.184
<i>Like a maple tree
in the fall...</i>

91
00:07:55.393 --> 00:07:56.352
Oh. no.

92
00:07:56.561 --> 00:07:58.312
Too syrupy-

93
00:07:58.521 --> 00:08:01.399
Oh. so many colors!

94
00:08:01.607 --> 00:08:05.069
Yes!
Simple! To the point!

95
00:08:05.278 --> 00:08:06.863
<i>So many colors...</i>

96
00:08:07.071 --> 00:08:10.741
<i>Nothing is as dull as
slaying inside</i>

97
00:08:10.950 --> 00:08:12.410
Kid. that's great.

98
00:08:12.618 --> 00:08:15.329
Where did you learn to write
songs like that? Hee-hop!

99
00:08:15.538 --> 00:08:18.124
It's like you're seeing the
world for the first time.

100
00:08:18.332 --> 00:08:21.043
You've got music in you. little
buzzer. and what goes in...

101
00:08:21.252 --> 00:08:22.211
"Laaaa!"

102
00:08:22.420 --> 00:08:25.006
must come out.
Come on. try it.

103
00:08:25.214 --> 00:08:26.424
"Laaaa!"

104
00:08:26.632 --> 00:08:28.176
Ill-all!

105
00:08:28.384 --> 00:08:30.219
"Laaaa!"

106
00:08:31.804 --> 00:08:35.099
"Laaaaaaaa!"

107
00:08:36.434 --> 00:08:38.561
Uh. yeah.
Save some for later.

108
00:08:41.314 --> 00:08:44.484
- You're a funny green bee.
- Green bee?

109
00:08:46.402 --> 00:08:49.572
You are seeing the world
for the first time!

110
00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:50.948
Pardon me. little miss.

111
00:08:51.157 --> 00:08:53.159
Flip the grasshopper
is my name.

112
00:08:53.367 --> 00:08:54.869
Roaming the meadow
is my game.

113
00:08:55.077 --> 00:08:56.245
What's the meadow?

114
00:08:57.205 --> 00:08:58.331
What's the meadow?

115
00:08:58.539 --> 00:09:00.708
Kid. you got to get out more.
Hee-hop!

116
00:09:03.836 --> 00:09:05.505
There it is.

117
00:09:07.131 --> 00:09:10.718
The meadow...
my home.

118
00:09:10.927 --> 00:09:12.428
You live out here?

119
00:09:12.637 --> 00:09:15.389
Not just me. Lots of insects
live in the meadow.

120
00:09:15.598 --> 00:09:17.558
Big. small. funny. smelly.

121
00:09:17.767 --> 00:09:20.061
You name it.
It's everything you can see.

122
00:09:20.269 --> 00:09:24.023
Up. down. sky to ground from
your hive to the tulip beds.

123
00:09:24.232 --> 00:09:26.859
all the way
to Gorgo's hedge.

124
00:09:27.068 --> 00:09:30.613
Where no little bee
should ever go.

125
00:09:30.821 --> 00:09:31.906
Why?

126
00:09:32.114 --> 00:09:33.866
Because a giant
bug-eating monster

127
00:09:34.075 --> 00:09:35.660
named Gorgo lives there.

128
00:09:35.868 --> 00:09:38.329
But enough of that!
Where are your friends?

129
00:09:38.538 --> 00:09:40.039
Bees always travel in groups.

130
00:09:40.248 --> 00:09:42.458
I don't think
I have any friends.

131
00:09:42.667 --> 00:09:44.293
No one in the hive likes me.

132
00:09:45.419 --> 00:09:47.797
Maybe I'm just
bad at being a bee.

133
00:09:48.005 --> 00:09:49.632
Sounds serious.

134
00:09:49.840 --> 00:09:52.843
Hey! Hey. what are you--

135
00:09:53.052 --> 00:09:55.096
Do not disturb the
great Dr. Flippenstein.

136
00:09:55.304 --> 00:09:57.098
You got a good heart. kid.
Say "Ah".

137
00:09:57.306 --> 00:09:58.182
Ah.

138
00:09:58.391 --> 00:10:00.643
What do you know?
Bees do have teeth.

139
00:10:00.851 --> 00:10:02.395
Beeswax... Promising.

140
00:10:04.021 --> 00:10:08.568
In my professional opinion.
the diagnosis is bee positive.

141
00:10:08.776 --> 00:10:10.236
You're a good
little buzzer. kid.

142
00:10:10.444 --> 00:10:13.406
Don't let anyone
say otherwise.

143
00:10:13.614 --> 00:10:16.033
Maybe we should get you
back to the hive. little one.

144
00:10:16.242 --> 00:10:18.077
No. Flip. can't I stay?

145
00:10:19.912 --> 00:10:21.205
Hee-hop!

146
00:10:28.379 --> 00:10:30.214
Approaching marigold
coordinates.

147
00:10:30.423 --> 00:10:33.259
Commence pollen
collection procedure.

148
00:10:51.861 --> 00:10:52.778
What is it?

149
00:10:54.614 --> 00:10:56.157
Hornets!

150
00:10:56.365 --> 00:10:58.242
Hold on to your buckets!

151
00:11:04.415 --> 00:11:06.584
Why so shy?

152
00:11:10.463 --> 00:11:12.465
Well. well. well.

153
00:11:12.673 --> 00:11:15.301
What do we got here?
Greedy little fluff-balls

154
00:11:15.509 --> 00:11:17.845
nabbing all the pollen
for themselves.

155
00:11:18.054 --> 00:11:19.597
Hold onto your buckets!

156
00:11:19.805 --> 00:11:21.265
Thieving buzz boxes about!

157
00:11:21.474 --> 00:11:24.185
Take that back. you
hoity toity hivecrawler.

158
00:11:24.393 --> 00:11:26.562
Hornets don't steal.

159
00:11:26.771 --> 00:11:29.523
Go back where you came from.
pollen-pinchers.

160
00:11:29.732 --> 00:11:32.693
We're shaking in our shells.

161
00:11:32.902 --> 00:11:34.820
Lucky for you
I've got a camp to set up.

162
00:11:35.029 --> 00:11:37.865
See you around... neighbor.

163
00:11:41.911 --> 00:11:43.954
There goes the neighborhood.

164
00:11:46.874 --> 00:11:49.001
Hey. my bucket's gone.

165
00:11:49.210 --> 00:11:52.421
- You see? Dirty thieves.
- Back to the hive!

166
00:11:52.630 --> 00:11:54.465
We need to report
this to the Queen.

167
00:11:54.674 --> 00:11:56.008
<i>Oh dear.</i>

168
00:11:59.637 --> 00:12:01.430
No. Flip-Bug. can't I stay?

169
00:12:01.639 --> 00:12:02.765
It's all so big

170
00:12:02.973 --> 00:12:05.851
and sunshiney out here.
and it smells so nice.

171
00:12:06.060 --> 00:12:08.646
Here you go. little buzzer.
I've got to hop.

172
00:12:08.854 --> 00:12:10.731
Bees don't like other bugs
hanging around the hive.

173
00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:13.234
- No. I want to stay!
- Don't worry.

174
00:12:14.819 --> 00:12:16.570
you'll see it again soon.

175
00:12:17.613 --> 00:12:20.116
- Really?
- Sure! Flowers and bees

176
00:12:20.324 --> 00:12:22.910
go together
like spiders and legs.

177
00:12:23.119 --> 00:12:25.871
But if you really want the
low-down on the meadow.

178
00:12:26.080 --> 00:12:28.749
you just call old Flip.
You can find me...

179
00:12:28.958 --> 00:12:30.793
Bees don't talk to other bugs!

180
00:12:30.960 --> 00:12:33.129
It wasn't another bug.
he was Flip.

181
00:12:33.337 --> 00:12:35.214
See you next time.
Hee-hop!

182
00:12:35.423 --> 00:12:37.925
Wait!
Flip. I want to go with you.

183
00:12:38.134 --> 00:12:41.804
Bees don't leave the hive
on their own. Now back to work!

184
00:12:42.012 --> 00:12:45.349
"Bees don't. bees never.
working bees. blah-blah-blah..."

185
00:12:45.558 --> 00:12:47.184
Bugs!

186
00:13:05.578 --> 00:13:08.664
Buzz! Buzz! Buzz!

187
00:13:21.886 --> 00:13:23.804
As Royal Adviser.

188
00:13:24.013 --> 00:13:27.516
I must strongly advise you
to repel the hornets.

189
00:13:27.725 --> 00:13:29.393
But they did not attack us.

190
00:13:29.602 --> 00:13:31.979
Well. no. not yet.

191
00:13:32.188 --> 00:13:34.398
But if we let them
set up camp.

192
00:13:34.607 --> 00:13:36.984
all the other
hornet tribes will follow.

193
00:13:37.193 --> 00:13:39.320
They'll surely
turn our meadow

194
00:13:39.528 --> 00:13:41.614
into a big
horrible hornet's nest.

195
00:13:41.822 --> 00:13:44.617
They'll kill all the flowers
and bugs. And then...

196
00:13:44.825 --> 00:13:47.870
Oh. and then
they'll eat us.

197
00:13:48.078 --> 00:13:50.831
We must show them
who's in charge.

198
00:13:51.040 --> 00:13:54.335
I am in charge.
remember?

199
00:13:54.543 --> 00:13:56.587
Your Majesty...

200
00:14:01.926 --> 00:14:06.138
That's all of it. Your Majesty.
This year's royal jelly harvest.

201
00:14:11.769 --> 00:14:14.230
Crawley. what's the problem?

202
00:14:14.438 --> 00:14:16.565
It appears to be blocked.
Your Adviseyness.

203
00:14:16.774 --> 00:14:18.692
Of course it's blocked.
Unblock it.

204
00:14:18.901 --> 00:14:20.945
- Me? But...
- Just do it.

205
00:14:21.153 --> 00:14:22.488
Of course. Ma'am.

206
00:14:29.078 --> 00:14:30.663
The royal jelly!

207
00:14:33.499 --> 00:14:35.167
That smells yummy.

208
00:14:35.376 --> 00:14:38.295
"Yummy?" Do you realize
what you almost did?

209
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:40.840
This is a year's
supply of royal jelly. child.

210
00:14:41.048 --> 00:14:43.384
The Queen's life depends on it.

211
00:14:43.592 --> 00:14:45.886
She can't eat anything else.

212
00:14:46.095 --> 00:14:49.932
She can't eat anything else...

213
00:14:50.140 --> 00:14:51.225
Crawley...

214
00:14:51.433 --> 00:14:53.978
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

215
00:14:54.186 --> 00:14:56.230
Ladybugs aren't always ladies?

216
00:14:56.438 --> 00:14:59.984
I'm thinking this royal
jelly is the answer to our

217
00:15:00.192 --> 00:15:03.445
little problem
with the Queen.

218
00:15:03.654 --> 00:15:07.074
- I'm sorry. Miss Queen.
- My. that was quite an entrance.

219
00:15:07.283 --> 00:15:09.326
- Are you all right. my dear?
- Oh. yes.

220
00:15:09.535 --> 00:15:12.454
The flower-fluff was very soft.
And tasty.

221
00:15:16.876 --> 00:15:18.919
You're a wild one. aren't you?

222
00:15:19.128 --> 00:15:22.590
I can see I'm going to have
to keep an eye on you.

223
00:15:22.798 --> 00:15:24.174
Which eye. Miss Queen?

224
00:15:24.383 --> 00:15:26.552
Silence!
I told you to behave.

225
00:15:26.760 --> 00:15:29.763
And I told you to
take her to school.

226
00:15:31.015 --> 00:15:33.893
Er... of course. Your Majesty.

227
00:15:34.101 --> 00:15:35.519
Buzz. buzz. Buzzlina.

228
00:15:37.187 --> 00:15:38.814
You! School.

229
00:15:44.153 --> 00:15:46.405
The meadow
isn't all flowers and sunshine.

230
00:15:46.614 --> 00:15:49.575
There are dangers. too.
Like hornets.

231
00:15:49.783 --> 00:15:52.536
Hornets!
Hide. everyone!

232
00:15:54.538 --> 00:15:55.873
Hornets!

233
00:15:59.293 --> 00:16:01.712
- What was that?
- Oh. Willi!

234
00:16:01.921 --> 00:16:03.672
How will you ever
recognise a hornet

235
00:16:03.881 --> 00:16:05.466
if you're always
asleep in my class?

236
00:16:05.674 --> 00:16:08.510
Me? No. no. no.
That was just my eyes.

237
00:16:08.719 --> 00:16:10.012
They take a break sometimes.

238
00:16:11.764 --> 00:16:15.517
Stop that infernal racket.
Bees don't sing!

239
00:16:15.726 --> 00:16:16.936
But Why?

240
00:16:17.144 --> 00:16:19.396
Because singing
leads to playing.

241
00:16:19.605 --> 00:16:23.233
and playing leads to laziness.
And a lazy bee!

242
00:16:23.442 --> 00:16:25.319
Gorgo. the bee-munching

243
00:16:25.527 --> 00:16:28.155
hedge-monster.
just loves lazy bees.

244
00:16:29.615 --> 00:16:31.617
<i>Gorgo...</i>

245
00:16:32.868 --> 00:16:35.871
Thank you for that
colorful description.

246
00:16:36.080 --> 00:16:38.707
- We've been expecting you. Maya.
- Maya?

247
00:16:38.916 --> 00:16:40.960
Well. yes... That's your name.

248
00:16:41.168 --> 00:16:42.294
Really?

249
00:16:42.503 --> 00:16:44.046
Maya.

250
00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:45.798
I like that.

251
00:16:46.006 --> 00:16:47.299
Maya.

252
00:16:47.508 --> 00:16:50.177
Maya.
Maya the Bee.

253
00:16:51.345 --> 00:16:53.847
Come along. little one.
Take a seat.

254
00:16:54.056 --> 00:16:55.516
A word. Buzzlina.

255
00:16:55.724 --> 00:16:57.309
What are you doing?

256
00:16:57.518 --> 00:16:58.936
Sitting next to you.

257
00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:01.397
But nobody ever sits next to me.

258
00:17:01.605 --> 00:17:04.817
I mean. excellent choice.
Maya. I'm Willi.

259
00:17:05.025 --> 00:17:07.528
Stick with me.
I know lots of things.

260
00:17:07.736 --> 00:17:10.030
This is my third First Flight
coming up. you know.

261
00:17:10.239 --> 00:17:14.493
Wow.
You must know everything.

262
00:17:14.702 --> 00:17:16.704
You're not like any
other bee I've met.

263
00:17:18.247 --> 00:17:21.000
- I keep hearing that.
- No. no. no.

264
00:17:21.208 --> 00:17:22.751
I meant that
in a good way.

265
00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:26.088
- We can be First Flight buddies.
- I'd like that!

266
00:17:26.296 --> 00:17:28.882
Miss Teaching Bee. when do
we go on our First Flight?

267
00:17:29.091 --> 00:17:30.592
Silence. 396!

268
00:17:30.801 --> 00:17:32.594
My name is Maya.

269
00:17:34.138 --> 00:17:35.514
Patience. Maya.

270
00:17:35.723 --> 00:17:37.766
You must learn
about the dangers first.

271
00:17:37.975 --> 00:17:39.643
We were just talking
about hornets.

272
00:17:39.852 --> 00:17:41.020
What's a hornet?

273
00:17:41.228 --> 00:17:43.814
Why. just a
bee's worst enemy.

274
00:17:44.023 --> 00:17:45.941
Great big scaly things.

275
00:17:46.150 --> 00:17:49.403
with giant claws
and red eyes.

276
00:17:49.611 --> 00:17:51.697
They like nothing more

277
00:17:51.905 --> 00:17:55.743
than dipping baby-bees
in pollen dust for their supper.

278
00:17:57.369 --> 00:17:59.371
They change into horrible.

279
00:17:59.580 --> 00:18:01.915
howling beasts at night.

280
00:18:03.292 --> 00:18:06.503
Their disgusting fuzz
hides parasites

281
00:18:06.712 --> 00:18:09.381
that are trained
to attack hornets.

282
00:18:09.590 --> 00:18:11.800
And if you let them get close.

283
00:18:12.009 --> 00:18:16.305
they'll suck your soul
right out of your body.

284
00:18:22.144 --> 00:18:23.020
Sorry.

285
00:18:24.188 --> 00:18:27.274
Son. you're not going to cry.
are you?

286
00:18:27.483 --> 00:18:30.194
I haven't raised a
bee-baby. have I?

287
00:18:30.402 --> 00:18:32.321
Dad. I hate bees.

288
00:18:32.529 --> 00:18:34.490
That's my boy.

289
00:18:34.698 --> 00:18:36.450
Play safe and stay in camp.

290
00:18:36.658 --> 00:18:38.452
Bees roam all
over these parts.

291
00:18:38.660 --> 00:18:39.870
Dad. no fair!

292
00:18:40.079 --> 00:18:42.623
I want to see one of
those dirty soul-suckers.

293
00:18:42.831 --> 00:18:44.249
Maybe when
you're bigger. son.

294
00:18:44.458 --> 00:18:45.959
- I am big.
- Look what you've done!

295
00:18:46.168 --> 00:18:47.836
- I barely touched it!
- That's the third time today!

296
00:18:51.465 --> 00:18:54.718
By my shiny shell!
Slay where I can see you. son.

297
00:18:54.927 --> 00:18:56.887
- But. Dad...
- No buts!

298
00:18:57.096 --> 00:18:58.639
I said stay in camp.

299
00:18:58.847 --> 00:19:01.225
- Look what you did.
- Move your pincers. lazy bugs!

300
00:19:01.433 --> 00:19:04.019
I want this camp
up by nightfall!

301
00:19:04.228 --> 00:19:06.939
I'm big enough. Hey!
Who wants to join my secret

302
00:19:07.147 --> 00:19:08.440
Bug Hunters' Club?

303
00:19:09.608 --> 00:19:12.569
Scaredy bugs.
I'll go on my own. then!

304
00:19:15.697 --> 00:19:17.324
And remember. children.

305
00:19:17.533 --> 00:19:20.119
bugs eat bees and
they don't say please.

306
00:19:20.327 --> 00:19:23.956
And that's why we don't trust
any other bugs. Ever.

307
00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:25.415
But what if they're your friend

308
00:19:25.624 --> 00:19:27.042
or they're really.
really pretty?

309
00:19:27.251 --> 00:19:28.710
Or you need their help?

310
00:19:28.919 --> 00:19:32.256
I would rather die
than ask another hug for help.

311
00:19:32.464 --> 00:19:34.007
Isn't that kind of silly?

312
00:19:35.884 --> 00:19:37.761
I guess it is.

313
00:19:39.096 --> 00:19:40.430
Miss Cassandra!

314
00:19:41.431 --> 00:19:43.058
I'm warning you. 396.

315
00:19:43.267 --> 00:19:45.060
No more interruptions.

316
00:19:45.269 --> 00:19:46.854
Something you want to say.

317
00:19:47.062 --> 00:19:48.689
- 396?
- Uh-uh!

318
00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:50.816
Good.

319
00:19:54.278 --> 00:19:56.155
But I just met a nice bug
and he didn't eat me.

320
00:19:56.363 --> 00:19:57.865
How can the meadow be
so bad when it's so pretty?

321
00:19:58.073 --> 00:19:59.032
That doesn't
even make sense.

322
00:19:59.241 --> 00:20:00.826
And really. why are
hornets so awful

323
00:20:01.034 --> 00:20:02.035
if you haven't even
met them either?

324
00:20:02.244 --> 00:20:03.412
And who is Gorgo. anyway?

325
00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.414
Why can't I laugh or dance
or play or leave the hive

326
00:20:05.622 --> 00:20:06.707
when it feels so good?

327
00:20:06.915 --> 00:20:08.834
Just because of some dumb
old crinkle face who's

328
00:20:09.001 --> 00:20:10.294
a funny looking bee
and won't even

329
00:20:10.502 --> 00:20:12.671
- let you si-ing?
- Uh-oh.

330
00:20:15.174 --> 00:20:19.136
That's it!
You're banned from First Flight.

331
00:20:19.344 --> 00:20:21.221
And all other flights.

332
00:20:24.516 --> 00:20:26.852
Follow me. children.
Stay close.

333
00:20:27.060 --> 00:20:29.563
And remember to
flap those wings.

334
00:20:40.115 --> 00:20:41.992
Hey. what are
you doing here?

335
00:20:42.201 --> 00:20:44.369
Why aren't you
out with the others?

336
00:20:44.578 --> 00:20:47.039
I couldn't leave
you alone. could I?

337
00:20:48.874 --> 00:20:51.752
Oh. Willi.
you're my best friend ever.

338
00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:53.503
You're the best.

339
00:20:53.712 --> 00:20:55.839
And you're my first friend ever.

340
00:20:56.048 --> 00:20:58.091
- Huh?
- Nothing. Nothing.

341
00:21:02.888 --> 00:21:05.057
What's wrong with me. Willi?

342
00:21:05.265 --> 00:21:08.560
- Why don't I fit into this hive?
- Fitting in is easy.

343
00:21:08.769 --> 00:21:11.188
Just stop asking questions
and follow orders.

344
00:21:11.396 --> 00:21:13.148
That's what the rest of us do.

345
00:21:13.357 --> 00:21:15.275
Of course. then you
wouldn't be crazy.

346
00:21:15.484 --> 00:21:17.236
funny Maya anymore.

347
00:21:17.444 --> 00:21:20.030
You'll be like every
other buzzer.

348
00:21:20.239 --> 00:21:23.492
You're right. Willi.
I'm the problem. not the hive!

349
00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:25.744
I have to tell
the Royal Adviser.

350
00:21:25.953 --> 00:21:28.121
From now on.
I'll do as I'm told.

351
00:21:28.330 --> 00:21:30.582
Maybe don't say
that it was my idea.

352
00:21:30.791 --> 00:21:33.543
- Maya?
- She's gonna be so happy!

353
00:21:33.752 --> 00:21:34.920
Crawley?

354
00:21:35.128 --> 00:21:37.881
Crawley. you sniveling sneak.
show yourself.

355
00:21:38.090 --> 00:21:40.425
Here I am.
Your Advisorness.

356
00:21:40.634 --> 00:21:41.760
Is it done?

357
00:21:41.969 --> 00:21:43.095
Of course.

358
00:21:46.974 --> 00:21:48.433
Dear me. Crawley.

359
00:21:48.642 --> 00:21:52.688
You know. I think the hornets
have stolen the royal jelly.

360
00:21:52.896 --> 00:21:55.857
But isn't that the royal jelly?

361
00:21:56.066 --> 00:21:59.319
We must find the dirty thieves
and destroy their camp.

362
00:21:59.528 --> 00:22:00.612
Mustn't we?

363
00:22:01.571 --> 00:22:03.657
But they didn't steal it.

364
00:22:03.865 --> 00:22:05.158
- I know they didn't!

365
00:22:05.367 --> 00:22:07.995
But the others don't know that.
do they. Crawley?

366
00:22:12.582 --> 00:22:15.043
- There you are. Miss Adviser...
- 396?

367
00:22:15.252 --> 00:22:16.837
<i>I came to say...</i>

368
00:22:17.045 --> 00:22:18.839
What are you doing
with the royal jelly?

369
00:22:19.047 --> 00:22:20.507
Silence! I warned you!

370
00:22:20.716 --> 00:22:22.134
Bees don't ask questions.

371
00:22:22.342 --> 00:22:23.802
- Get out!
- Wait. Miss Advisorness.

372
00:22:24.011 --> 00:22:25.012
You were right.

373
00:22:25.220 --> 00:22:27.889
- I have to learn all your rules.
- Impossible.

374
00:22:28.098 --> 00:22:30.267
There's no place in this hive
for troublemakers.

375
00:22:30.475 --> 00:22:31.893
No. I can change.

376
00:22:32.102 --> 00:22:35.022
- I promise I'll try.
- Forget it. 396.

377
00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:36.940
You don't belong here.

378
00:22:37.149 --> 00:22:39.985
You are banished
from this hive.

379
00:22:40.193 --> 00:22:43.196
Banished...
But where will I go?

380
00:22:43.405 --> 00:22:47.492
It's the meadow for
wretched little bugs like you.

381
00:22:47.701 --> 00:22:49.411
Good. I like bugs!

382
00:22:49.619 --> 00:22:52.706
They're a lot nicer
than you. you big bully!

383
00:22:52.914 --> 00:22:54.791
Then go. 396.

384
00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:57.336
I'm sure there's a
meadow full of bugs

385
00:22:57.544 --> 00:22:59.796
just waiting to meet you.

386
00:23:01.298 --> 00:23:02.966
Or eat you.

387
00:23:05.927 --> 00:23:07.637
Mean old bully bee.

388
00:23:07.846 --> 00:23:08.972
I'll show you.

389
00:23:09.181 --> 00:23:12.017
There's a place for me
out here somewhere.

390
00:23:26.323 --> 00:23:27.407
Okay...

391
00:23:36.792 --> 00:23:37.751
Maya?

392
00:23:45.300 --> 00:23:47.219
<i>Hey! I'm flying!</i>

393
00:23:52.724 --> 00:23:56.395
But I don't think little bees
can survive out in the meadow.

394
00:23:56.603 --> 00:23:58.063
Exactly.

395
00:23:58.271 --> 00:24:03.777
Go after her and see
that nature takes its course.

396
00:24:03.985 --> 00:24:05.278
Oh. no.

397
00:24:05.487 --> 00:24:08.407
You have to save her. Willi.
No. She'll be all right.

398
00:24:08.615 --> 00:24:11.326
No. she won't.
Just do it.

399
00:24:11.535 --> 00:24:14.579
Maya!
Wait. Maya!

400
00:24:14.788 --> 00:24:15.747
Maya!

401
00:24:52.075 --> 00:24:54.202
Hello. meadow!
I'm here.

402
00:24:55.912 --> 00:24:58.165
Oh. a shiny plant.

403
00:24:58.373 --> 00:25:00.208
Hey. that's not nice.

404
00:25:26.485 --> 00:25:29.613
I'm coming to save you. Maya.

405
00:25:29.821 --> 00:25:31.072
Willi?

406
00:25:47.255 --> 00:25:49.382
Don't worry. Willi's here.

407
00:25:49.591 --> 00:25:51.384
It's me. Willi!

408
00:25:51.593 --> 00:25:53.762
Maya.
What are you doing out here?

409
00:25:53.970 --> 00:25:57.557
I've left the hive. Willi.
and I'm never ever coming back.

410
00:25:57.766 --> 00:26:00.435
Yeah. right. Right.
Good one.

411
00:26:00.644 --> 00:26:01.353
You what?!

412
00:26:02.687 --> 00:26:05.148
The Royal Adviser says
I don't belong there.

413
00:26:05.357 --> 00:26:10.320
But so far I haven't been doing
so well out here. either.

414
00:26:10.529 --> 00:26:13.782
I don't think I fit
in anywhere. Willi.

415
00:26:13.990 --> 00:26:15.909
Maya. you're a bee.

416
00:26:16.117 --> 00:26:17.536
Bees live in hives.

417
00:26:17.744 --> 00:26:19.120
Even I know that.

418
00:26:19.329 --> 00:26:21.206
You can't survive out here
on your own.

419
00:26:21.414 --> 00:26:23.375
Well. I'm not on
my own now.

420
00:26:23.583 --> 00:26:25.210
Oh. great!
That's just great.

421
00:26:25.418 --> 00:26:26.878
We'll both get eaten!

422
00:26:27.087 --> 00:26:28.171
- Flip!
- No!

423
00:26:28.380 --> 00:26:30.215
Now you're flipping out on me?

424
00:26:30.423 --> 00:26:33.343
No.
Flip the crazy grass jumper.

425
00:26:33.552 --> 00:26:35.345
He knows how to
live in the meadow.

426
00:26:35.554 --> 00:26:37.013
He can show me where I fit in.

427
00:26:37.222 --> 00:26:39.015
I'm not going back
out there in the dark.

428
00:26:39.224 --> 00:26:41.226
We'll have to wait
until the morning.

429
00:26:43.270 --> 00:26:46.189
If we get eaten tonight.
I'll never forgive you.

430
00:26:54.739 --> 00:26:57.284
Did the frogs get her?

431
00:26:57.492 --> 00:26:59.411
Of course. Ma'am.

432
00:26:59.619 --> 00:27:01.204
Excellent.

433
00:27:05.542 --> 00:27:07.669
Maya? Willi?

434
00:27:09.546 --> 00:27:10.964
Kids!

435
00:27:22.767 --> 00:27:24.894
Grub. leaf. rock.

436
00:27:25.103 --> 00:27:26.479
Leaf covers rock.

437
00:27:26.688 --> 00:27:27.939
You learn quickly.

438
00:27:28.148 --> 00:27:30.817
- Grub. leaf. rock.
- I win again.

439
00:27:31.026 --> 00:27:33.820
Nom. nom. nom.
Caterpillar eats your leaf.

440
00:27:34.029 --> 00:27:36.489
You look outside first.

441
00:27:36.698 --> 00:27:40.285
Well. I would have looked first
even ill had won.

442
00:27:40.493 --> 00:27:42.537
That's just the
kind of bee I am.

443
00:27:48.126 --> 00:27:50.420
- What is it. Willi?
- A monster.

444
00:27:50.629 --> 00:27:54.049
With big eyes and fangs.
ready to eat us.

445
00:27:57.552 --> 00:27:58.803
How pretty.

446
00:27:59.012 --> 00:28:00.597
Are you sure
that's a monster. Willi?

447
00:28:00.805 --> 00:28:03.933
Is it gone? Don't worry.
I shooed it away.

448
00:28:04.142 --> 00:28:07.937
- With an attack shriek.
- Thank you. my protector.

449
00:28:08.146 --> 00:28:12.192
So where is this flippity
grass jumper of yours?

450
00:28:12.400 --> 00:28:14.402
Somewhere in the meadow.

451
00:28:14.611 --> 00:28:15.904
That narrows it down.

452
00:28:16.112 --> 00:28:19.407
I guess we'll need to ask
some bugs for directions.

453
00:28:19.616 --> 00:28:22.661
Maya...
You're so going to get us eaten.

454
00:28:25.538 --> 00:28:27.082
Son!

455
00:28:27.290 --> 00:28:30.335
Son? Son!

456
00:28:30.543 --> 00:28:31.878
Son?

457
00:28:32.087 --> 00:28:33.129
Boy!

458
00:28:33.338 --> 00:28:36.591
Sweet cola cans.
Where's my little nipper got to?

459
00:28:36.800 --> 00:28:37.550
Hey. wake up!

460
00:28:38.760 --> 00:28:41.346
How can you sleep
when my boy's missing?

461
00:28:41.554 --> 00:28:43.056
- What's he missing. boss?
- What? I

462
00:28:43.264 --> 00:28:45.725
No. he's missing!
I can't find him.

463
00:28:45.934 --> 00:28:47.644
He must have
snuck out last night.

464
00:28:47.852 --> 00:28:50.772
Let's move out!
And I mean everybody. out!

465
00:28:50.980 --> 00:28:52.482
I want my boy back!

466
00:28:55.819 --> 00:28:56.986
Son!

467
00:29:01.366 --> 00:29:03.284
Wait. Maya.

468
00:29:03.493 --> 00:29:05.036
I'm hungry again.

469
00:29:05.245 --> 00:29:08.081
Come on. Willi.
We've got to find Flip.

470
00:29:08.289 --> 00:29:09.541
I'm tired.

471
00:29:09.749 --> 00:29:13.336
- You're always tired.
- I'm a growing bee.

472
00:29:14.796 --> 00:29:16.506
I need my sleep.

473
00:29:17.966 --> 00:29:19.968
There's something
under that leaf.

474
00:29:20.176 --> 00:29:24.681
- Maybe it knows where Flip is.
- Maya! What are you doing?

475
00:29:24.889 --> 00:29:28.560
He doesn't look too dangerous.
He's stripy and little like us.

476
00:29:28.768 --> 00:29:31.980
- But kind of shiny. too.
- I'm not little.

477
00:29:32.188 --> 00:29:34.733
- Hello.
- Hey. get your own leaf.

478
00:29:36.234 --> 00:29:38.987
We're looking for a big green
crazy bug called Flip.

479
00:29:39.195 --> 00:29:41.614
- Have you seen him?
- Huh. baby stuff.

480
00:29:41.823 --> 00:29:43.408
I'm looking for...

481
00:29:43.616 --> 00:29:45.618
No. I can't tell you.

482
00:29:45.827 --> 00:29:47.287
Unless

483
00:29:47.495 --> 00:29:50.039
you join my secret
Bug Hunters' Club.

484
00:29:50.248 --> 00:29:51.875
No. Maya.
There's an old hive saying:

485
00:29:52.041 --> 00:29:53.334
"No clubs with strange bugs."

486
00:29:53.543 --> 00:29:55.628
Who're you calling
strange. fuzz face?

487
00:29:55.837 --> 00:29:58.298
- We're in!
- I like you.

488
00:29:58.506 --> 00:30:00.133
You've got guts.

489
00:30:00.341 --> 00:30:04.429
Okay. Hold onto your stripes.
Cause I'm hunting the greediest.

490
00:30:04.637 --> 00:30:07.182
most disgustingest
bugs in the meadow.

491
00:30:07.390 --> 00:30:10.393
Honey guzzling soul-suckers.

492
00:30:10.602 --> 00:30:12.562
Oh. yeah!
I want to meet these nice bugs.

493
00:30:12.771 --> 00:30:14.230
No. you don't!
No. she doesn't!

494
00:30:14.439 --> 00:30:17.317
Let's go. Bug Hunters!
Danger calls.

495
00:30:20.779 --> 00:30:22.822
What kind of bug are you.
anyway?

496
00:30:23.031 --> 00:30:24.866
The best kind. Sting.

497
00:30:25.074 --> 00:30:27.660
"Stink-Bug."
Yeah. good one.

498
00:30:27.869 --> 00:30:30.580
- Really. though. what are you?
- What do you think? I'm a...

499
00:30:30.789 --> 00:30:32.582
- Hornets!
- Hornets?

500
00:30:32.791 --> 00:30:35.543
- Son!
- Oh. no. Dad.

501
00:30:35.752 --> 00:30:37.879
- Hornets!
- Really? - Why?

502
00:30:38.087 --> 00:30:41.424
Hide. Maya! They'll munch you!
Tell her. Stink-Bug.

503
00:30:41.633 --> 00:30:43.259
Stink-Bug?

504
00:30:43.468 --> 00:30:45.470
I thought he was our new friend.

505
00:30:45.678 --> 00:30:48.473
The hornets got him. Maya.
And we're next!

506
00:30:48.681 --> 00:30:51.309
There's an old bee saying:

507
00:30:51.518 --> 00:30:53.520
"Stay in the hive. stay alive."

508
00:30:55.605 --> 00:30:57.982
These are dark times. bees.

509
00:30:58.191 --> 00:31:00.568
The hive is in grave danger.

510
00:31:00.777 --> 00:31:04.614
Today hornets broke in
and stole our royal jelly.

511
00:31:04.823 --> 00:31:09.077
We must get it back.
The Queen's life depends on it.

512
00:31:09.285 --> 00:31:10.787
But we have no proof.

513
00:31:12.080 --> 00:31:15.250
Crawley. I think the
Queen needs to lie down.

514
00:31:15.458 --> 00:31:18.294
- This way. Your Majesty.
- We mustn't jump to conclusions.

515
00:31:18.503 --> 00:31:20.964
It's time we showed
those grubby hornets

516
00:31:21.172 --> 00:31:23.675
who runs this meadow.

517
00:31:24.884 --> 00:31:25.927
Wait!

518
00:31:26.135 --> 00:31:29.180
Maya and Willi
have disappeared.

519
00:31:29.389 --> 00:31:31.391
They must have gone outside.

520
00:31:31.599 --> 00:31:33.351
I'm no nursemaid.

521
00:31:33.560 --> 00:31:35.436
Babies are your department.

522
00:31:35.645 --> 00:31:39.482
Now if you don't mind
I've got a hive to save.

523
00:31:39.691 --> 00:31:42.277
No. Wait. Wait!

524
00:31:42.485 --> 00:31:44.362
We have to do something.

525
00:31:44.571 --> 00:31:45.864
Please.

526
00:31:48.616 --> 00:31:50.118
Well. tickle my pincers!

527
00:31:50.326 --> 00:31:52.161
I never thought I'd see the day

528
00:31:52.370 --> 00:31:54.497
when a bee would
ask an ant for help.

529
00:31:54.706 --> 00:31:56.624
Oh please. Colonel.

530
00:31:56.833 --> 00:31:58.418
Don't worry. ma'am.
We'll find them.

531
00:31:58.626 --> 00:32:00.712
Men! We're looking
for two baby bees.

532
00:32:00.920 --> 00:32:04.674
Fuzzy. stripey. boogly eyes
and bobbly heads. Get it?

533
00:32:04.883 --> 00:32:06.759
Boogly eyes and
bobbly heads. Sir!

534
00:32:06.968 --> 00:32:09.137
Good.
Bart. Bert. that way!

535
00:32:09.345 --> 00:32:10.763
Tex. Lex. that way!

536
00:32:10.972 --> 00:32:12.557
Troy. Trey. over there!

537
00:32:13.433 --> 00:32:14.559
Arnie...

538
00:32:14.767 --> 00:32:16.352
...and Barney.

539
00:32:16.561 --> 00:32:17.979
- Yes. Sir!
- Reporting for duty. Sir!

540
00:32:18.187 --> 00:32:20.982
- Turn around! No. not you. the--
- Yes. Sir!

541
00:32:21.190 --> 00:32:23.860
- Turn around. you on the left!
- Yes. Sir!

542
00:32:24.068 --> 00:32:25.737
I meant my left!

543
00:32:25.945 --> 00:32:28.072
Your left when you're facing us.
Sir. or when you're facing away?

544
00:32:28.281 --> 00:32:29.616
- Sir?
- Oh. forget it.

545
00:32:29.824 --> 00:32:31.743
Sir!
Forgetting it now. Sir.

546
00:32:38.750 --> 00:32:40.376
<i>Just go...</i>

547
00:32:40.585 --> 00:32:42.128
somewhere over that way.

548
00:32:42.337 --> 00:32:44.839
And don't break anything!
I order you

549
00:32:45.048 --> 00:32:46.925
- not to break anything.
- Yes. Sir!

550
00:32:47.133 --> 00:32:48.801
You can count on us. Sir.
not to break anything.

551
00:32:49.010 --> 00:32:50.345
Sir. Sir yes Sir!
Breaking everything. Sir!

552
00:32:50.553 --> 00:32:51.971
No. we've got to
not break anything.

553
00:32:52.180 --> 00:32:53.598
Not breaking everything. Sir!

554
00:32:53.806 --> 00:32:56.017
- My foot!
- I'll thump you...

555
00:32:57.018 --> 00:32:59.103
- Attention!
- Yes. Sir!

556
00:33:00.521 --> 00:33:03.608
- Just go.
- Yes. Sir!

557
00:33:03.816 --> 00:33:05.485
Hut. hut. hut. hut. hut.
hut. hut. hut. hut. hut...

558
00:33:08.863 --> 00:33:12.283
Sir. request permission
to ask a question. Sir.

559
00:33:12.492 --> 00:33:13.910
Go ahead. soldier.

560
00:33:14.118 --> 00:33:16.329
What was the
mission again. Sir?

561
00:33:18.373 --> 00:33:21.417
Find those little bees!

562
00:33:23.544 --> 00:33:25.713
<i>Round and round and round!</i>

563
00:33:25.922 --> 00:33:28.091
I've got a bad feeling
about this.

564
00:33:28.299 --> 00:33:29.801
And I don't
frighten easily.

565
00:33:30.009 --> 00:33:31.511
Oh. don't be a fluff belly.

566
00:33:31.719 --> 00:33:33.012
They sound tiny.

567
00:33:33.221 --> 00:33:33.763
Hello!

568
00:33:35.431 --> 00:33:39.602
Don't be scared. little ones.
We just need some directions.

569
00:33:39.811 --> 00:33:41.896
Okay. No one there.
Let's go.

570
00:33:42.105 --> 00:33:43.231
Oh. Willi. Come on!

571
00:33:44.273 --> 00:33:45.566
Visitors!

572
00:33:46.401 --> 00:33:49.028
Say hello. my children.

573
00:33:49.237 --> 00:33:50.738
Hello!

574
00:33:50.947 --> 00:33:53.616
Just in time for breakfast.

575
00:33:53.825 --> 00:33:55.743
And I'm hungry.

576
00:33:57.161 --> 00:34:00.999
What about you guys?
We've got some rotten fruit.

577
00:34:01.207 --> 00:34:03.376
So. what brings you
little pollinators

578
00:34:03.584 --> 00:34:04.919
to the House of Moth?

579
00:34:05.128 --> 00:34:07.797
We're. um. looking for
a bug called Flip.

580
00:34:08.006 --> 00:34:09.257
The grasshopper?

581
00:34:09.465 --> 00:34:10.591
Cool!

582
00:34:10.800 --> 00:34:12.885
He'll be cutting loose
at the big party.

583
00:34:13.094 --> 00:34:15.388
A party?
How do we get there?

584
00:34:15.596 --> 00:34:17.682
Easy.
Wait for the sun to set.

585
00:34:17.890 --> 00:34:20.727
then fly straight
till you find a bright light.

586
00:34:20.935 --> 00:34:24.647
and just go round and
round and round...

587
00:34:26.482 --> 00:34:29.027
I think we need
different directions. Willi.

588
00:34:29.235 --> 00:34:30.278
I agree.

589
00:34:32.947 --> 00:34:34.699
Maybe he knows
where the party is.

590
00:34:34.907 --> 00:34:37.118
No. Maya.
That's a dung beetle.

591
00:34:37.326 --> 00:34:38.786
They say one
whiff of that ball

592
00:34:38.995 --> 00:34:40.663
can knock a bee
right out of the sky.

593
00:34:40.872 --> 00:34:42.749
How bad can it be?

594
00:34:45.334 --> 00:34:48.379
Excuse me. Mr. Dung-Roller.

595
00:34:48.588 --> 00:34:52.592
What?
But... nobody ever talks to me.

596
00:34:52.800 --> 00:34:54.469
We're looking for the big party.

597
00:34:54.677 --> 00:34:57.430
I never get invited to parties.

598
00:34:57.638 --> 00:35:00.183
Apparently I've got odor issues.

599
00:35:00.391 --> 00:35:03.644
- You could come with us.
- Oh. thanks. Littlun'.

600
00:35:03.853 --> 00:35:07.273
But not all insects take as
kindly as you to old Kurt.

601
00:35:07.482 --> 00:35:08.483
You go on. though.

602
00:35:08.691 --> 00:35:11.110
Parties usually happen
at Jitterbug Hollow.

603
00:35:11.319 --> 00:35:13.029
I'll show you the way.
First you've got to...

604
00:35:13.237 --> 00:35:14.489
Here. hold this.

605
00:35:14.697 --> 00:35:17.575
So. to get to Jitterbug Hollow.
you follow this trench

606
00:35:17.784 --> 00:35:19.494
then you turn
left at the daisies.

607
00:35:19.702 --> 00:35:20.995
And when you
get to the river.

608
00:35:21.204 --> 00:35:23.623
you've got to follow it all the
way around Gorgo's hedge.

609
00:35:23.831 --> 00:35:26.250
My ball!
Whatever you do.

610
00:35:26.459 --> 00:35:29.504
don't go through Spider Forest!

611
00:35:29.712 --> 00:35:33.132
Go through
Spider Forest. got it.

612
00:35:33.341 --> 00:35:33.966
Maya. you stink.

613
00:35:35.093 --> 00:35:36.928
- You want a hug. Willi?
- No no no.

614
00:35:37.136 --> 00:35:39.388
- No. No!
- Give me a hug!

615
00:35:39.597 --> 00:35:42.266
- Help! Help!
- Come back here. Willi!

616
00:35:42.475 --> 00:35:46.562
- Hut. hut. hut. hut. hut. hut...
- That's it!

617
00:35:46.771 --> 00:35:49.148
Any more huts and
we'd be a village.

618
00:35:49.357 --> 00:35:50.650
Where are we?

619
00:35:50.858 --> 00:35:53.986
Shh! I'm picking up bee vibes.
And something else. too.

620
00:35:55.613 --> 00:35:58.116
Kind of strong-smelling...

621
00:35:58.324 --> 00:35:59.992
Pollen? Is it pollen?

622
00:36:00.201 --> 00:36:01.828
Where there's bees.
there's always pollen.

623
00:36:02.036 --> 00:36:03.454
That's got to be pollen.

624
00:36:03.663 --> 00:36:06.457
Pollen!
Come to Papa!

625
00:36:11.379 --> 00:36:13.673
This doesn't smell like pollen.

626
00:36:15.258 --> 00:36:17.218
And it certainly doesn't
taste like pollen.

627
00:36:25.184 --> 00:36:29.522
"Oh. it's easy. just go
through the Spider Forest."

628
00:36:29.730 --> 00:36:33.151
What kind oi sick. twisted
dung beetle was he?

629
00:36:33.359 --> 00:36:36.571
See? I told you. Maya.
The dung got to his head.

630
00:36:39.157 --> 00:36:41.909
- Hi. Bug Hunters.
- Sting Bug!

631
00:36:42.118 --> 00:36:44.704
We're closing in on those
ugly soul-suckers.

632
00:36:44.912 --> 00:36:45.997
Oh. good--

633
00:36:46.205 --> 00:36:48.124
"Goody?"
There are spiders

634
00:36:48.332 --> 00:36:50.209
and monsters
in this forest. Maya.

635
00:36:50.418 --> 00:36:52.670
Aw! You're not going
to cry. are you?

636
00:36:52.879 --> 00:36:54.755
Anyone would think you
were a bee baby!

637
00:36:54.964 --> 00:36:56.215
Well. er...

638
00:36:56.424 --> 00:36:57.633
Thank you?

639
00:36:58.301 --> 00:36:59.635
Think. Willi.

640
00:36:59.844 --> 00:37:01.095
What is he?

641
00:37:04.932 --> 00:37:09.937
Spiky antennas.
spiky feet. spiky tail.

642
00:37:10.146 --> 00:37:11.272
<i>Just like...</i>

643
00:37:11.480 --> 00:37:12.064
<i>a...</i>

644
00:37:12.773 --> 00:37:14.650
- hornet!
- Where?

645
00:37:14.859 --> 00:37:17.737
Him! There was a picture
just like him in the hive.

646
00:37:17.945 --> 00:37:20.239
But where are
his big red eyes?

647
00:37:20.448 --> 00:37:22.867
And isn't he a bit small?

648
00:37:23.075 --> 00:37:24.368
I'm not small.

649
00:37:24.577 --> 00:37:25.786
Wait a minute.

650
00:37:25.995 --> 00:37:28.247
Hive?
You're bees?

651
00:37:28.456 --> 00:37:31.292
Get back!
Don't suck my soul!

652
00:37:33.711 --> 00:37:36.130
Look!
He's changing colour!

653
00:37:37.506 --> 00:37:41.177
Run. Maya! He's turning
into a spider monster!

654
00:37:41.385 --> 00:37:42.803
A spider what?

655
00:37:44.847 --> 00:37:47.350
Hello. little ones.

656
00:37:47.558 --> 00:37:49.852
- You look lost!
- No. no. no. no!

657
00:37:50.061 --> 00:37:53.231
Care to join me for dinner?

658
00:37:53.439 --> 00:37:55.483
I'm not hungry.

659
00:37:56.567 --> 00:38:00.029
Help! I'm serious!
Help me! Guys?

660
00:38:00.238 --> 00:38:02.240
- We have to save him.
- No. Maya.

661
00:38:02.448 --> 00:38:05.117
- We'll be spider food.
- Not if she can't catch us.

662
00:38:05.326 --> 00:38:09.497
- Hey. what are you doing?
- Four wings are faster than two.

663
00:38:09.705 --> 00:38:11.165
I really need some
help here. guys!

664
00:38:11.374 --> 00:38:13.459
You flap your wings. I'll steer.

665
00:38:13.668 --> 00:38:16.337
- Why do you get to steer?
- Don't leave me!

666
00:38:16.545 --> 00:38:17.630
We're coming!

667
00:38:22.510 --> 00:38:23.886
Grab him!

668
00:38:24.804 --> 00:38:27.390
Don't worry. we'll save you!

669
00:38:38.818 --> 00:38:39.777
Bees!

670
00:38:41.153 --> 00:38:44.532
You follow and you follow
and you don't give up.

671
00:38:44.740 --> 00:38:48.869
And that. my friend. is the key
to being a great tracker.

672
00:38:49.078 --> 00:38:50.830
You know. Barney.
you are so full of--

673
00:38:51.038 --> 00:38:53.791
Shh! I'm definitely
picking up bee vi...

674
00:38:53.958 --> 00:38:57.128
Vibes.
It's pronounced <i>vi...</i>

675
00:38:57.336 --> 00:38:59.046
<i>Vi... Hey!</i>

676
00:38:59.839 --> 00:39:01.882
Hey!

677
00:39:02.091 --> 00:39:03.634
Respect. Brother Sun.

678
00:39:03.843 --> 00:39:07.471
We gratefully
accept your bounty.

679
00:39:07.680 --> 00:39:11.475
- Say hello. my children.
- Hello!

680
00:39:13.853 --> 00:39:15.521
Now. where were we?

681
00:39:17.481 --> 00:39:20.151
Oh. yeah!
Bright lights...

682
00:39:20.359 --> 00:39:24.363
- We were going round and round.
- And round. and round...

683
00:39:33.289 --> 00:39:34.623
That was close.

684
00:39:34.832 --> 00:39:37.084
Next time you
save someone's life.

685
00:39:37.293 --> 00:39:39.670
try not to kill them.

686
00:39:41.297 --> 00:39:43.716
Saved by a
pair of bee-babies...

687
00:39:43.924 --> 00:39:46.385
- What's Dad gonna say?
- "Thank you?"

688
00:39:46.594 --> 00:39:48.137
You don't know my Dad.

689
00:39:48.346 --> 00:39:50.389
And we don't want to.
Leave him. Maya.

690
00:39:50.598 --> 00:39:51.724
No. Willi. wait.

691
00:39:51.932 --> 00:39:53.768
We can't just leave
him here like this.

692
00:39:53.976 --> 00:39:55.102
Maya. we need to find

693
00:39:55.311 --> 00:39:56.812
Jitterbug Hollow
before it gets dark.

694
00:39:57.021 --> 00:40:00.649
Wait. Jitterbug Hollow?
It's near my camp.

695
00:40:00.858 --> 00:40:02.818
- I can take you.
- We don't need your help.

696
00:40:03.027 --> 00:40:04.862
We know exactly
where we're going.

697
00:40:05.071 --> 00:40:06.072
Somewhere that way!

698
00:40:06.280 --> 00:40:10.701
- You mean into Gorgo's land?
- Gorgo?

699
00:40:10.910 --> 00:40:13.621
If you get me out of here
I'll show you the way.

700
00:40:13.829 --> 00:40:15.581
No. Maya.
It's a trap.

701
00:40:15.790 --> 00:40:19.043
But Willi. he knows the way.
And there's a party. remember.

702
00:40:19.251 --> 00:40:21.087
- I bet there's pollen...
- Pollen?

703
00:40:21.295 --> 00:40:22.129
<i>...and buttercups.</i>

704
00:40:22.338 --> 00:40:24.006
- Let's go!
...and nectar!

705
00:40:24.215 --> 00:40:27.343
Come on. let's go!
What are we waiting for?

706
00:40:27.551 --> 00:40:30.137
What about your dad?
Won't he be worried?

707
00:40:30.346 --> 00:40:31.430
My Dad worried?

708
00:40:32.556 --> 00:40:35.267
He's. like. the
toughest guy ever.

709
00:40:36.727 --> 00:40:39.563
My boy... where is he?

710
00:40:39.772 --> 00:40:41.190
Ah. boss?

711
00:40:41.399 --> 00:40:43.609
- Something in my eye.
- Look!

712
00:40:46.529 --> 00:40:48.572
Turn around. daisy-sniffers!

713
00:40:48.781 --> 00:40:50.491
You're on hornet turf!

714
00:40:50.699 --> 00:40:52.618
Bee turf!
You paper-chewers

715
00:40:52.827 --> 00:40:55.413
have until first light to
leave our meadow.

716
00:40:55.621 --> 00:40:59.041
Oh. really?
Hornets budge for no bug.

717
00:40:59.250 --> 00:41:01.210
What do you
think of that. huh?

718
00:41:02.920 --> 00:41:04.755
You'll see.

719
00:41:04.964 --> 00:41:07.675
Get out of here before
I de-fuzz the lot of you!

720
00:41:07.883 --> 00:41:09.051
You've been warned.

721
00:41:09.260 --> 00:41:11.262
There will be consequences.

722
00:41:12.596 --> 00:41:15.266
Who's afraid of those
striped puff-balls?

723
00:41:15.474 --> 00:41:16.934
Keep looking! Son!

724
00:41:17.143 --> 00:41:18.227
Son!

725
00:41:18.727 --> 00:41:20.146
Son!

726
00:41:34.410 --> 00:41:35.703
I've got it.

727
00:41:37.371 --> 00:41:38.664
Ha-ha!

728
00:41:39.415 --> 00:41:41.459
- Mine!
- No. mine!

729
00:41:41.667 --> 00:41:42.626
Mine...

730
00:41:42.835 --> 00:41:44.503
Gimme. gimme!
I saw it first!

731
00:41:51.760 --> 00:41:53.304
Hornets...

732
00:41:54.013 --> 00:41:55.681
Okay. okay. okay.

733
00:41:55.890 --> 00:41:58.642
Remember our training.
Touch nothing.

734
00:41:58.851 --> 00:42:01.770
Leave everything
exactly as we found--

735
00:42:13.532 --> 00:42:14.283
<i>Oooh...</i>

736
00:42:15.117 --> 00:42:17.036
Maybe they won't notice.

737
00:42:36.972 --> 00:42:39.391
Jitterbug Hollow!

738
00:42:39.600 --> 00:42:41.185
Dragonfly rides!

739
00:42:41.393 --> 00:42:42.937
Dragonfly rides!

740
00:42:43.145 --> 00:42:45.981
Get your dragonfly rides here!

741
00:42:49.193 --> 00:42:50.069
Awesome.

742
00:42:51.153 --> 00:42:53.531
- Want a ride. kid?
- Maybe later.

743
00:42:53.739 --> 00:42:55.241
Anytime.

744
00:42:56.659 --> 00:42:58.619
Well? So where
is this Flip?

745
00:42:58.827 --> 00:42:59.912
It's starting.

746
00:43:08.420 --> 00:43:11.507
- Ladybugs and garden pests!
- Look!

747
00:43:13.175 --> 00:43:16.804
Welcome to Jitterbug Hollow!

748
00:43:17.012 --> 00:43:18.556
Hit it. Mozz!

749
00:43:20.558 --> 00:43:22.726
Let's get some melody!

750
00:43:25.229 --> 00:43:27.648
Now... bugbox!

751
00:43:30.651 --> 00:43:33.904
Let's hear it for the misfits!

752
00:43:34.113 --> 00:43:37.366
What an audience
we've got tonight.

753
00:43:37.575 --> 00:43:39.868
Worms. gnats.
crickets. horseflies.

754
00:43:40.077 --> 00:43:41.161
Why the long faces?

755
00:43:41.370 --> 00:43:43.247
- Any bugs here from out of town?
- Me. Flip!

756
00:43:43.455 --> 00:43:45.833
- Hey. Flip. it's me!
- Welcome. little one.

757
00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:48.377
- Did they give you a name yet?
- Maya.

758
00:43:48.586 --> 00:43:51.046
Maya? I like it.

759
00:43:51.255 --> 00:43:54.174
What brings you
to Jitterbug Hollow. Maya?

760
00:43:54.383 --> 00:43:58.304
Well. you said ii I ever had a
question I should come to you.

761
00:43:58.512 --> 00:44:01.724
Ask away.
We're all friends here.

762
00:44:03.392 --> 00:44:05.185
Where do I belong. Flip?

763
00:44:06.103 --> 00:44:08.147
Oh. an easy one.

764
00:44:08.355 --> 00:44:11.859
Last I checked. bees
belonged in hives. Maya.

765
00:44:12.067 --> 00:44:15.529
They don't like me back there.
I'm just too different.

766
00:44:15.738 --> 00:44:18.782
Please. Flip. you need to
leach me how to live out here.

767
00:44:18.991 --> 00:44:20.242
In the meadow.

768
00:44:20.451 --> 00:44:22.202
Here. Hold this.

769
00:44:22.411 --> 00:44:26.332
Maya. the answers
you seek are in here.

770
00:44:26.540 --> 00:44:28.626
Step inside the magic flower

771
00:44:28.834 --> 00:44:30.377
and be transformed

772
00:44:30.586 --> 00:44:34.340
into the bug that
everyone loves!

773
00:44:34.548 --> 00:44:37.176
Behold the mysteries
of the meadow

774
00:44:37.384 --> 00:44:39.970
as I transform Maya.

775
00:44:40.179 --> 00:44:42.348
You say ci-cay-da.
I say ci-cah-da...

776
00:44:43.807 --> 00:44:47.102
Well. little buzzer.
how do you feel?

777
00:44:47.311 --> 00:44:50.022
Huh? Hey!
I'm still the same.

778
00:44:50.230 --> 00:44:51.523
Exactly.

779
00:44:51.732 --> 00:44:53.400
You don't need my help.

780
00:44:53.609 --> 00:44:55.527
- Huh?
- Just be yourself

781
00:44:55.736 --> 00:44:58.113
and you'll make it anywhere.

782
00:44:58.322 --> 00:45:01.617
Let's make this little buzzer
feel welcome.

783
00:45:04.787 --> 00:45:06.580
<i>The grass is always greener</i>

784
00:45:06.789 --> 00:45:09.041
<i>in some other insect's yard.</i>

785
00:45:09.249 --> 00:45:11.502
<i>Just look across Just look across
the big fence now the big fence now</i>

786
00:45:11.710 --> 00:45:13.379
<i>You'll see it's not so hard!</i>

787
00:45:13.587 --> 00:45:14.797
<i>It's not so hard!</i>

788
00:45:15.005 --> 00:45:17.091
<i>It's easy to let those big bees</i>

789
00:45:17.299 --> 00:45:19.468
<i>make you feel make you feel
a little bit small.</i>

790
00:45:19.677 --> 00:45:21.720
<i>Just keep you head
held high now.</i>

791
00:45:21.929 --> 00:45:24.973
<i>Now don't you feel...
taller than tall?</i>

792
00:45:29.728 --> 00:45:33.649
<i>- It don't matter what they say!
- It don't matter!</i>

793
00:45:33.857 --> 00:45:38.529
<i>Find that rhythm in your heart!
Just bee yourself every day!</i>

794
00:45:38.737 --> 00:45:40.948
<i>Shake your bee-hind all about!</i>

795
00:45:41.156 --> 00:45:43.158
<i>Shake-shake... Shake it out...</i>

796
00:45:43.367 --> 00:45:47.746
<i>Shout it out!
And bee yourself every day!</i>

797
00:45:50.666 --> 00:45:52.960
<i>Ask your new friends
around you!</i>

798
00:45:53.168 --> 00:45:55.295
<i>they flew from near and far!</i>

799
00:45:55.504 --> 00:45:57.589
<i>We come from the
same bug family!</i>

800
00:45:57.798 --> 00:45:59.967
<i>And we love you
the way you are!</i>

801
00:46:00.175 --> 00:46:02.469
<i>Life's all about the
bugs who love you!</i>

802
00:46:02.678 --> 00:46:04.888
<i>Good if lends can
be hard to find...</i>

803
00:46:05.097 --> 00:46:07.307
<i>Red beetle. blue beetle!
Big smelly dung beetle!</i>

804
00:46:07.516 --> 00:46:10.102
<i>It don't matter what
their kind!</i>

805
00:46:10.310 --> 00:46:12.062
<i>It don't matter what
they say!</i>

806
00:46:13.772 --> 00:46:18.777
<i>Find that rhythm in your heart!
Just bee yourself every day!</i>

807
00:46:18.986 --> 00:46:22.948
<i>- Shake your bee-hind all about.
- Shake. shake! Shake it out!</i>

808
00:46:23.157 --> 00:46:28.704
<i>Say it loud. shout it out.
and bee yourself every day!</i>

809
00:46:28.912 --> 00:46:32.458
Remember. Maya:
What goes in must come out.

810
00:46:32.666 --> 00:46:33.959
"Laaaa!"

811
00:46:34.918 --> 00:46:37.129
"Laaaa!"

812
00:46:37.337 --> 00:46:39.089
<i>I wanna sing songs.</i>

813
00:46:39.298 --> 00:46:41.467
<i>I want to be free.</i>

814
00:46:41.675 --> 00:46:43.802
<i>I wanna be me.</i>

815
00:46:44.011 --> 00:46:47.723
<i>- I'm Maya the Bee-ee!
- Maya!</i>

816
00:46:53.270 --> 00:46:55.731
<i>I am Maya the Bee!</i>

817
00:46:56.982 --> 00:46:58.567
You're a star. Maya.

818
00:46:58.776 --> 00:47:02.529
C'mon. I'll show you
how to move your bee-hind.

819
00:47:02.738 --> 00:47:04.198
You. Me. Dance floor.

820
00:47:08.994 --> 00:47:11.038
<i>Sing out loud!
Shout it out!</i>

821
00:47:11.246 --> 00:47:13.081
<i>- And bee yourself!
- Son!</i>

822
00:47:21.632 --> 00:47:22.591
Yeah!

823
00:47:25.093 --> 00:47:27.554
Away from that bee! Now!

824
00:47:28.472 --> 00:47:30.516
What has she done to you?

825
00:47:30.724 --> 00:47:32.434
My Buzzywump is the
bee-hatingest

826
00:47:32.643 --> 00:47:33.977
hornet in the meadow.

827
00:47:34.186 --> 00:47:37.731
Undo your evil hive magic.
I'm warning you.

828
00:47:40.359 --> 00:47:43.904
Your name is "Buzzywump"?

829
00:47:44.112 --> 00:47:45.364
It's a good name.

830
00:47:46.114 --> 00:47:48.242
Dad. I can explain.

831
00:47:48.450 --> 00:47:50.118
She and him...

832
00:47:50.327 --> 00:47:53.247
They kinda sorta...
saved my life.

833
00:47:53.455 --> 00:47:55.791
But it's not like we're
friends or anything.

834
00:47:59.670 --> 00:48:02.506
I'm sensing a lot of tension
here. You're all bugged out.

835
00:48:02.714 --> 00:48:05.217
Done to pieces.
Are you eating properly?

836
00:48:05.425 --> 00:48:09.555
Come on. Hank.
she saved your boy.

837
00:48:09.763 --> 00:48:12.850
This happy hopper just saved
you a stinging. bee-nut!

838
00:48:13.058 --> 00:48:16.019
But keep away from my son.

839
00:48:16.228 --> 00:48:18.063
Oh. boy.
you are so grounded.

840
00:48:18.272 --> 00:48:20.440
Any more grounded
and you'd be a worm.

841
00:48:24.152 --> 00:48:25.487
It's okay.

842
00:48:25.696 --> 00:48:28.532
He's just a mixed-up
little bug like you were.

843
00:48:28.740 --> 00:48:30.200
He'll learn.

844
00:48:30.409 --> 00:48:32.035
I hope so.

845
00:48:36.874 --> 00:48:39.042
- Royal Adviser?
- Yes?

846
00:48:40.252 --> 00:48:42.379
I mean. come in!
Did you...

847
00:48:42.588 --> 00:48:46.258
- give the hornets my message?
- They won't leave the meadow...

848
00:48:46.466 --> 00:48:48.427
- Ma'am.
- Excellent.

849
00:48:49.887 --> 00:48:51.680
Dismissed. sergeant.

850
00:48:55.976 --> 00:48:57.102
Crawley?

851
00:48:57.311 --> 00:49:00.689
Yes. Your Sneakiness?
I mean Your Schemingness.

852
00:49:00.898 --> 00:49:02.524
It's time.

853
00:49:02.733 --> 00:49:06.111
You brought this on
yourself. old buzzer.

854
00:49:06.320 --> 00:49:08.739
I wish there were another way.
We need...

855
00:49:08.947 --> 00:49:11.325
a strong leader.
And you are just...

856
00:49:11.533 --> 00:49:13.785
too weak.

857
00:49:13.994 --> 00:49:17.956
Crawley? Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

858
00:49:18.165 --> 00:49:20.667
It depends on what you're
thinking. Your Thinkyness.

859
00:49:27.174 --> 00:49:29.176
Your Majesty!

860
00:49:47.319 --> 00:49:50.614
Nice legwork. Mr. Centipede.
See you next time.

861
00:49:50.822 --> 00:49:53.492
Alright. you flies.
No more eating vomit.

862
00:49:53.700 --> 00:49:55.827
Oh. there you are.
Come on.

863
00:49:56.036 --> 00:49:58.372
Flip is ready to take us home.

864
00:49:58.580 --> 00:49:59.748
I am home. Willi.

865
00:50:01.041 --> 00:50:05.671
- Here? In the meadow?
- This is where I belong.

866
00:50:05.879 --> 00:50:09.257
With stink bugs and
smelly. stinky hornets?

867
00:50:09.466 --> 00:50:11.927
No. With all bugs.

868
00:50:12.135 --> 00:50:14.471
With all bugs
except me. huh?

869
00:50:14.680 --> 00:50:17.182
Don't be cross.
I'll visit you.

870
00:50:17.391 --> 00:50:19.893
Why would you visit
boring old Willi

871
00:50:20.102 --> 00:50:23.188
in his boring old hive
when you've got all this?

872
00:50:23.397 --> 00:50:26.483
I put my stinger
on the line for you.

873
00:50:26.692 --> 00:50:30.445
- And this is how you thank me?
- But. Willi...

874
00:50:30.654 --> 00:50:33.615
With all your new bug friends
I guess you won't need

875
00:50:33.824 --> 00:50:35.742
poor old Willi anymore.

876
00:50:35.951 --> 00:50:37.285
Don't be silly.

877
00:50:37.494 --> 00:50:38.912
Stay with me.

878
00:50:39.121 --> 00:50:40.831
There's an old bee saying:

879
00:50:41.039 --> 00:50:43.250
"You can always
count on a friend."

880
00:50:43.458 --> 00:50:45.752
But I guess I got that
one wrong. too.

881
00:50:45.961 --> 00:50:48.588
Willi!
Willi!

882
00:51:04.730 --> 00:51:08.108
Son. I know you think
you like that bee.

883
00:51:08.316 --> 00:51:09.776
but she's
twisted your thoughts.

884
00:51:09.985 --> 00:51:11.361
Dad. not all bees are--

885
00:51:11.570 --> 00:51:14.573
Shh. It's quiet.
Too quiet.

886
00:51:23.665 --> 00:51:25.917
By my pointy pincers!

887
00:51:27.127 --> 00:51:30.047
Pollen...
This is bee work.

888
00:51:30.255 --> 00:51:33.925
Those sneaky wax-nibblers
set us up.

889
00:51:34.134 --> 00:51:36.219
Didn't I say you
can't trust bees?

890
00:51:36.428 --> 00:51:37.262
<i>But Dad...</i>

891
00:51:37.471 --> 00:51:38.972
Assemble the Five Tribes!

892
00:51:39.181 --> 00:51:41.683
If those fur-balls
want to play rough.

893
00:51:41.892 --> 00:51:44.352
they picked on the
wrong hornets!

894
00:51:46.063 --> 00:51:47.397
Oh. no.

895
00:51:51.234 --> 00:51:55.155
Whoa. If this is Jitterbug
Hollow. I'm a flea.

896
00:51:55.363 --> 00:51:56.907
We're lost. Antstein.

897
00:51:57.115 --> 00:51:58.283
You're lost. bug-brain.

898
00:51:58.492 --> 00:52:00.994
My feelers know exactly
where we are.

899
00:52:05.207 --> 00:52:06.792
Oh. yeah? Where?

900
00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:08.835
Wait. wait. wait. Wait.

901
00:52:09.044 --> 00:52:12.214
I'm getting something.
Bee vibes.

902
00:52:12.422 --> 00:52:15.092
- Excuse us. fellas.
- Everybody. shh!

903
00:52:15.300 --> 00:52:18.303
Yep. yep. Definitely a bee
around here somewhere.

904
00:52:18.512 --> 00:52:20.097
Is it Willi?

905
00:52:20.305 --> 00:52:22.349
- We're looking for a bee. too.
- That's great. kid.

906
00:52:22.557 --> 00:52:23.725
A little shush. please.

907
00:52:23.934 --> 00:52:25.227
Genius at work!

908
00:52:25.435 --> 00:52:27.521
Arnie. hey. Arnie. look.

909
00:52:27.729 --> 00:52:30.899
Fuzzy. stripy.
boogly eyes and bobbly head!

910
00:52:31.108 --> 00:52:33.151
- A tigerfly!
- No. a bee.

911
00:52:33.360 --> 00:52:34.778
- Oh. a bee!
- A bee!

912
00:52:34.986 --> 00:52:38.073
And Flip! Hey. Arnie. didn't I
say we were on the right track?

913
00:52:38.281 --> 00:52:39.825
- Where've you been. naughty bee?

914
00:52:40.033 --> 00:52:41.743
Miss Cassandra's got enough
worries without you

915
00:52:41.952 --> 00:52:43.036
buzzing off into the meadow.

916
00:52:43.245 --> 00:52:44.621
Hey. don't you know
the Queen's sick?

917
00:52:44.830 --> 00:52:47.249
The hornets stole
her royal jelly.

918
00:52:55.465 --> 00:52:58.677
It was the Adviser.
I saw her with the royal jelly.

919
00:52:58.885 --> 00:53:01.096
Flip. we need to
get back to the hive.

920
00:53:01.304 --> 00:53:03.849
- Willi!
- Good work. boys.

921
00:53:04.057 --> 00:53:05.100
Hee-hop!

922
00:53:06.810 --> 00:53:10.522
- Willi!
- Willi! Where are you?

923
00:53:10.730 --> 00:53:12.732
Willi!

924
00:53:15.610 --> 00:53:17.863
"I am home. Willi.

925
00:53:18.071 --> 00:53:20.532
"Here at Jitterbug Hollow
I'm so happy."

926
00:53:20.740 --> 00:53:25.203
Fine. be like that. I'll go home
too. and I'll feel happy.

927
00:53:25.412 --> 00:53:29.457
Back to your pond. froggy.
I'm not in the mood.

928
00:53:29.666 --> 00:53:33.879
- We've got pollen!
- Oh. pollen.

929
00:53:34.087 --> 00:53:37.465
No.
No. Willi. Stay strong.

930
00:53:37.674 --> 00:53:40.010
But you'll be
stronger with pollen.

931
00:53:41.511 --> 00:53:42.762
No! No. no. no. no. no.

932
00:53:42.971 --> 00:53:44.681
Walk on. Willi. Walk on.

933
00:53:44.890 --> 00:53:46.349
Okay. you win.

934
00:53:46.558 --> 00:53:48.268
Gimme gimme gimme
gimme pollen!

935
00:53:52.814 --> 00:53:55.192
Willi?
Willi. come back.

936
00:53:55.400 --> 00:53:57.652
He's caught in an updraft!

937
00:53:57.861 --> 00:53:59.863
Those are big flutter bugs.

938
00:54:00.071 --> 00:54:01.489
They're not flutter bugs.

939
00:54:01.698 --> 00:54:03.241
they're bats!

940
00:54:05.785 --> 00:54:10.457
We have to do something!
When I count to three. kick!

941
00:54:10.665 --> 00:54:11.875
One. two. three.

942
00:54:12.083 --> 00:54:13.001
Hee-hop!

943
00:54:18.924 --> 00:54:20.800
Nice birdy.

944
00:54:21.009 --> 00:54:23.011
Hold on. Willi.
I'm coming!

945
00:54:30.644 --> 00:54:33.438
I'm coming. kids! Hee-hop!

946
00:54:35.941 --> 00:54:37.943
Hey. ugly!
Over here!

947
00:54:43.573 --> 00:54:45.951
Maya!
Hold on. kids!

948
00:55:17.983 --> 00:55:19.943
You kids okay?

949
00:55:22.279 --> 00:55:23.655
Willi!

950
00:55:25.490 --> 00:55:26.908
Willi?

951
00:55:27.993 --> 00:55:29.244
No. no.

952
00:55:29.452 --> 00:55:30.996
Please wake up.

953
00:55:35.208 --> 00:55:37.502
You said you had pollen.

954
00:55:37.711 --> 00:55:38.962
Oh. Willi.

955
00:55:40.130 --> 00:55:43.425
I am so sorry.
Are you still my friend?

956
00:55:43.633 --> 00:55:46.886
Of course. You must never
let a friend go. Maya.

957
00:55:47.095 --> 00:55:50.849
Especially your
best and only friend.

958
00:55:53.143 --> 00:55:55.979
- Where are we?
- Shh. Gorgo's hedge.

959
00:55:56.187 --> 00:55:58.189
Gorgo's hedge?

960
00:55:58.398 --> 00:56:01.359
- Which way is the hive. Flip?
- We're going back to the hive?

961
00:56:01.568 --> 00:56:03.945
Straight through Gorgo's land.
No. no. no!

962
00:56:04.154 --> 00:56:06.239
Maya. go all
the way around.

963
00:56:06.448 --> 00:56:08.033
- Yeah. listen to him!
- There's no time!

964
00:56:08.241 --> 00:56:09.492
This is the quickest way.

965
00:56:09.701 --> 00:56:11.453
I'm confused.
What's going on?

966
00:56:11.661 --> 00:56:13.955
The Queen needs us. Willi.
I'll tell you on the way.

967
00:56:14.164 --> 00:56:17.167
She's got more spark then a
barrel full of lightning bugs.

968
00:56:17.375 --> 00:56:18.293
Hee-hop!

969
00:56:20.295 --> 00:56:22.797
We're gonna get eaten.
I know it.

970
00:56:30.263 --> 00:56:31.639
Royal bees!

971
00:56:31.848 --> 00:56:33.767
I regret to inform you

972
00:56:33.975 --> 00:56:35.560
that after a long
battle with illness

973
00:56:35.769 --> 00:56:37.437
our beloved Queen

974
00:56:37.645 --> 00:56:40.190
is not quite one
hundred percent.

975
00:56:40.398 --> 00:56:43.360
That is to say. well.
she has buzzed off

976
00:56:43.568 --> 00:56:45.779
to the big hive in the sky.

977
00:56:46.654 --> 00:56:49.115
She has passed away.

978
00:56:51.034 --> 00:56:53.995
But every hive
needs a strong leader.

979
00:56:54.204 --> 00:56:56.039
And that is why I.

980
00:56:56.247 --> 00:56:58.124
your new hive master.

981
00:56:58.333 --> 00:57:01.461
am honored
to announce our new Queen.

982
00:57:01.669 --> 00:57:03.380
Buzzlina.

983
00:57:03.588 --> 00:57:06.633
the Conqueror!

984
00:57:11.346 --> 00:57:14.974
- Is it true?
- My dear bees.

985
00:57:15.183 --> 00:57:19.979
let us pause to remember
our beloved leader.

986
00:57:20.188 --> 00:57:25.235
We all know who is responsible
for this grave injustice:

987
00:57:25.443 --> 00:57:27.779
The filthy hornets.

988
00:57:27.987 --> 00:57:32.951
First our poor gentle Queen.
and next our hive.

989
00:57:33.159 --> 00:57:36.037
Are we going to let them
get away with it?

990
00:57:36.246 --> 00:57:38.415
- No!
- At first light.

991
00:57:38.623 --> 00:57:43.628
we'll run those horrid
buzz-boxes out of our meadow.

992
00:57:43.837 --> 00:57:46.172
This is for the Queen!

993
00:57:46.381 --> 00:57:47.549
Oh. no.

994
00:57:47.757 --> 00:57:50.301
Maya and Willi are out there.

995
00:57:55.807 --> 00:57:57.851
That's Gorgo's belly.

996
00:57:58.059 --> 00:58:00.228
He's hungry. Maya.
We should turn back.

997
00:58:00.437 --> 00:58:02.480
Come on. Willi.

998
00:58:02.689 --> 00:58:04.065
Wait for us. Maya.

999
00:58:04.274 --> 00:58:05.859
Don't go too far ahead.

1000
00:58:12.157 --> 00:58:14.784
- Gorgo's got Maya!
- Maya? Come on!

1001
00:58:19.080 --> 00:58:20.498
Gorgo wants to eat us!

1002
00:58:20.707 --> 00:58:22.417
- Get off. greedy guts.
- Hey!

1003
00:58:22.625 --> 00:58:25.795
- Over here!
- Maya...

1004
00:58:26.004 --> 00:58:28.298
Gorgo is going to
be really. really cross.

1005
00:58:28.506 --> 00:58:30.675
You should never. ever
land on a monster.

1006
00:58:30.884 --> 00:58:32.552
It's just common sense.

1007
00:58:32.760 --> 00:58:34.596
Gorgo's not a monster. Willi.

1008
00:58:34.804 --> 00:58:36.139
She's right.

1009
00:58:36.347 --> 00:58:39.350
This is what everybody's
so scared of?

1010
00:58:39.559 --> 00:58:41.769
He's made out of grass.

1011
00:58:41.978 --> 00:58:45.398
A grass monster?
They're the worst.

1012
00:58:48.026 --> 00:58:50.153
Hold on!

1013
00:58:51.988 --> 00:58:53.156
Willi!

1014
00:58:55.283 --> 00:58:56.242
Maya!

1015
00:58:57.619 --> 00:58:58.745
Maya!

1016
00:59:06.794 --> 00:59:07.795
Maya!

1017
00:59:09.297 --> 00:59:10.924
A baby Gorgo!

1018
00:59:11.132 --> 00:59:14.219
Enough is enough.
Payback time.

1019
00:59:19.390 --> 00:59:20.558
Willi...

1020
00:59:20.767 --> 00:59:22.810
- What are you doing?
- Maya?

1021
00:59:23.019 --> 00:59:25.188
Kids!
Are you okay?

1022
00:59:25.396 --> 00:59:28.942
- Kind of.
- I tip my hat to you. Maya.

1023
00:59:29.150 --> 00:59:31.945
You taught this old bug
something new.

1024
00:59:32.153 --> 00:59:36.449
Come on. before
poor old Gorgo falls on us!

1025
00:59:42.622 --> 00:59:44.541
I am a dirty bee monster.

1026
00:59:44.749 --> 00:59:47.502
- I've come to suck your soul.
- Stop that.

1027
00:59:47.710 --> 00:59:48.962
Bees don't suck souls.

1028
00:59:49.170 --> 00:59:51.339
Some of them are
even kind of nice.

1029
00:59:51.548 --> 00:59:53.299
Sting's a bee-lover.

1030
00:59:58.930 --> 01:00:01.432
The Five Tribes!

1031
01:00:02.433 --> 01:00:03.977
Welcome. my brothers!

1032
01:00:04.185 --> 01:00:06.104
Eat. dance and be feral.

1033
01:00:06.312 --> 01:00:08.606
Because at first light tomorrow

1034
01:00:08.815 --> 01:00:13.736
we'll gonna squash those pollen
guzzlers once and for all!

1035
01:00:16.364 --> 01:00:18.616
Oh. no. Maya!

1036
01:00:32.088 --> 01:00:34.507
Halt! Bees only!

1037
01:00:34.716 --> 01:00:36.426
But we have to
speak to the Queen.

1038
01:00:36.634 --> 01:00:38.428
How do we know
you're not a hornet spy?

1039
01:00:38.636 --> 01:00:42.265
How do we know you're not a
frog in fluffy pyjamas?

1040
01:00:42.473 --> 01:00:44.475
- Tough crowd.
- Sorry.

1041
01:00:44.684 --> 01:00:46.519
- Queen's orders.
- Flip!

1042
01:00:46.728 --> 01:00:49.480
You go. Maya.
I'll be right out here.

1043
01:00:52.150 --> 01:00:54.611
All gather in the great hall.

1044
01:00:58.156 --> 01:00:59.324
Ahh!

1045
01:00:59.532 --> 01:01:02.118
- Oh! Hey!
- Out of the way!

1046
01:01:02.327 --> 01:01:04.871
I don't think I like
this hive anymore.

1047
01:01:09.125 --> 01:01:11.210
How do we get past
the queen's guards?

1048
01:01:11.419 --> 01:01:14.213
Don't worry. Maya.
I got this.

1049
01:01:14.422 --> 01:01:17.842
Hey. you guys.
check this out.

1050
01:01:18.051 --> 01:01:19.052
Willi...

1051
01:01:30.855 --> 01:01:32.315
Nice moves.

1052
01:01:32.523 --> 01:01:34.150
Heh. bye.

1053
01:01:38.071 --> 01:01:40.281
Your Majesty.
You're better.

1054
01:01:42.784 --> 01:01:43.910
396?

1055
01:01:44.118 --> 01:01:44.952
<i>But...</i>

1056
01:01:45.161 --> 01:01:46.537
But it's not possible.

1057
01:01:46.746 --> 01:01:48.665
Why's the golden hat
on your head?

1058
01:01:48.873 --> 01:01:49.749
Where is the Queen?

1059
01:01:50.875 --> 01:01:52.669
You're looking at her.
Guards!

1060
01:01:52.877 --> 01:01:55.463
- What have you done?
- Coming. Your Highness!

1061
01:01:55.672 --> 01:01:57.048
Hot honey cakes.

1062
01:01:58.007 --> 01:01:59.258
Just the way
you like them.

1063
01:02:00.718 --> 01:02:02.929
Maya. you're alive! That's...

1064
01:02:04.138 --> 01:02:05.932
very. very
serious indeed.

1065
01:02:06.140 --> 01:02:08.976
Don't you know?
Our dear Queen...

1066
01:02:09.185 --> 01:02:11.020
- has passed away.
- No!

1067
01:02:11.229 --> 01:02:14.023
Don't you worry. 396.

1068
01:02:14.232 --> 01:02:17.318
We'll have our revenge
on those ghastly hornets.

1069
01:02:17.527 --> 01:02:21.447
Liar! You stole the royal jelly
from the queen and hid it.

1070
01:02:24.701 --> 01:02:27.620
It's true. I'm guilty.

1071
01:02:29.372 --> 01:02:31.874
Guilty of caring too much:

1072
01:02:32.083 --> 01:02:33.751
Against my better judgment

1073
01:02:33.960 --> 01:02:37.880
I let this mixed-up little bee
go into the meadow alone.

1074
01:02:38.089 --> 01:02:41.300
Poor child. she's not
in her right mind.

1075
01:02:41.509 --> 01:02:44.137
Wait! She's lying.
You have to believe me.

1076
01:02:44.345 --> 01:02:47.014
I know where she
hid the royal jelly.

1077
01:02:47.223 --> 01:02:50.143
Well. if you're so sure.
why don't you show us

1078
01:02:50.351 --> 01:02:51.644
where it is?

1079
01:02:53.855 --> 01:02:56.441
This is it. in here.

1080
01:02:57.525 --> 01:03:00.278
Poor little bee's
got meadow fever.

1081
01:03:00.486 --> 01:03:03.364
Now everyone can see
what a liar you are.

1082
01:03:07.201 --> 01:03:08.703
Huh? But where is it?

1083
01:03:08.911 --> 01:03:11.581
- Lock her up.
- No. let go.

1084
01:03:11.789 --> 01:03:15.418
- She's lying.
- It's for your own good. 396.

1085
01:03:15.626 --> 01:03:20.465
Now if you'll excuse me.
I've got some hornets to crush.

1086
01:03:20.673 --> 01:03:23.092
- I promise. she took it!
- This way.

1087
01:03:23.301 --> 01:03:25.344
No. let go.
She's lying.

1088
01:03:25.553 --> 01:03:26.304
No!

1089
01:03:27.764 --> 01:03:31.559
No. the hornets didn't do it!
Please believe me.

1090
01:03:31.768 --> 01:03:33.936
I told you she was a liar.

1091
01:03:35.813 --> 01:03:37.231
Give me that!

1092
01:03:55.291 --> 01:03:57.168
Your Majesty!

1093
01:03:59.504 --> 01:04:01.047
Coming.

1094
01:04:06.010 --> 01:04:07.512
- Willi.
- Maya.

1095
01:04:07.720 --> 01:04:08.638
Willi. Willi!

1096
01:04:09.972 --> 01:04:12.850
I'll have you out of there
in two wingbeats.

1097
01:04:14.977 --> 01:04:16.521
Make that
three wingbeats.

1098
01:04:17.730 --> 01:04:19.690
- You're not supposed to be here!
- Willi!

1099
01:04:19.899 --> 01:04:23.444
What are you doing here?
Stop!

1100
01:04:23.653 --> 01:04:24.904
Stop!

1101
01:04:26.948 --> 01:04:29.200
Stop!
Come back!

1102
01:04:32.286 --> 01:04:33.955
Grab him!

1103
01:04:35.957 --> 01:04:36.958
Traitor!

1104
01:04:37.166 --> 01:04:39.669
- Stop that tubby dunce.
- Stop!

1105
01:04:44.382 --> 01:04:46.551
Left. right. left. right...

1106
01:04:58.145 --> 01:05:01.899
This is a waste of time.
We have bugs to crush.

1107
01:05:13.035 --> 01:05:14.704
Fall in. soldier.

1108
01:05:21.752 --> 01:05:23.671
- Willi...
- Keep moving!

1109
01:05:25.673 --> 01:05:27.383
Keep formation!

1110
01:05:28.217 --> 01:05:31.387
Willi!
Don't go away.

1111
01:05:34.599 --> 01:05:36.767
Don't leave me.

1112
01:06:06.297 --> 01:06:08.215
Flip!
Flip!

1113
01:06:16.807 --> 01:06:19.518
- Get off me. bug!
- Flip. help!

1114
01:06:19.727 --> 01:06:21.520
Wait. is that Willi!

1115
01:06:21.729 --> 01:06:23.314
Stink Bug?

1116
01:06:24.565 --> 01:06:26.025
You have to warn your Queen.

1117
01:06:26.233 --> 01:06:28.027
Dad's making an
ambush on the hive.

1118
01:06:28.235 --> 01:06:31.322
But the bees are making
an ambush on you hornets.

1119
01:06:31.530 --> 01:06:33.199
Flip!

1120
01:06:41.332 --> 01:06:42.291
Hello?

1121
01:06:43.584 --> 01:06:44.669
Who's there?

1122
01:06:45.586 --> 01:06:48.089
Miss Queen?
Miss Queen.

1123
01:06:48.297 --> 01:06:49.924
You're alive.
Your Majesty.

1124
01:06:50.132 --> 01:06:52.176
- It's me. Maya.
- Maya?

1125
01:06:53.469 --> 01:06:56.263
It's okay. I'm going
to get us out of here.

1126
01:07:01.978 --> 01:07:06.273
No. no. no. stay with me.
Please.

1127
01:07:06.482 --> 01:07:08.150
I'm sorry. Miss Queen.

1128
01:07:08.359 --> 01:07:09.986
It's my fault.

1129
01:07:10.194 --> 01:07:14.782
I just wanted to see
the outside world.

1130
01:07:14.991 --> 01:07:18.035
If I had stayed in the hive
like a good bee.

1131
01:07:18.244 --> 01:07:21.330
I could have
stopped the Adviser.

1132
01:07:22.999 --> 01:07:26.002
It's not your fault. Maya.

1133
01:07:26.919 --> 01:07:29.547
You followed your heart.

1134
01:07:29.755 --> 01:07:31.465
That takes courage.

1135
01:07:32.633 --> 01:07:34.010
<i>You stay...</i>

1136
01:07:34.218 --> 01:07:36.345
just the way you are.

1137
01:07:37.513 --> 01:07:39.473
- Maya...

1138
01:07:39.682 --> 01:07:42.059
No. Wake up.

1139
01:07:44.478 --> 01:07:47.898
- Maya.
- Willi! You came back.

1140
01:07:49.275 --> 01:07:50.693
And Sting.

1141
01:07:51.777 --> 01:07:53.612
I'm sorry about what I said.

1142
01:07:53.821 --> 01:07:54.780
I didn't mean it.

1143
01:07:54.989 --> 01:07:57.033
You're the best
friend a hornet

1144
01:07:57.241 --> 01:07:59.076
- could have.
- Maya...

1145
01:07:59.285 --> 01:08:01.620
Thank sweet nectar you're safe!

1146
01:08:01.829 --> 01:08:03.330
How did you know I was here?

1147
01:08:03.539 --> 01:08:05.166
A charming grasshopper.

1148
01:08:05.374 --> 01:08:06.959
a fiery hornet

1149
01:08:07.168 --> 01:08:11.672
and a brave little bee snuck in
and told me everything.

1150
01:08:11.881 --> 01:08:13.215
Your Majesty...

1151
01:08:13.424 --> 01:08:14.675
Stay with us.

1152
01:08:15.551 --> 01:08:17.053
She's fading fast.

1153
01:08:17.261 --> 01:08:20.222
- She needs the royal jelly.
- The Royal Adviser took it.

1154
01:08:20.431 --> 01:08:22.516
How are we going to
get it back from her?

1155
01:08:22.725 --> 01:08:23.934
It's not gonna be easy.

1156
01:08:24.143 --> 01:08:26.604
All the hornet tribes are going
up against the bees.

1157
01:08:26.812 --> 01:08:28.272
Take me to them.

1158
01:08:28.481 --> 01:08:32.026
Only I can stop this.

1159
01:08:32.234 --> 01:08:34.236
- We could carry her.
- Too slow.

1160
01:08:34.445 --> 01:08:36.739
We'll never catch
the bees in time.

1161
01:08:36.947 --> 01:08:37.865
I'll do it.

1162
01:08:38.074 --> 01:08:40.159
I'll go ahead and
get the royal jelly.

1163
01:08:40.367 --> 01:08:42.912
- You follow me with the Queen.
- No. Maya.

1164
01:08:43.120 --> 01:08:46.207
It's too dangerous.
You're just one little bee.

1165
01:08:46.415 --> 01:08:49.376
- Two little bees.
- And a hornet.

1166
01:08:49.585 --> 01:08:52.088
And a whole meadow
full of friends.

1167
01:08:52.296 --> 01:08:55.257
If anyone can do it. she can.

1168
01:08:55.466 --> 01:08:57.510
You really keep
surprising me.

1169
01:08:57.718 --> 01:09:00.137
I'm so proud of you. Maya.

1170
01:09:00.346 --> 01:09:01.305
Be careful.

1171
01:09:02.515 --> 01:09:05.935
Let's go. Bug Hunters!
Danger calls!

1172
01:09:40.344 --> 01:09:41.887
We're flying ants!

1173
01:09:45.599 --> 01:09:48.644
There they are!
There's still time. Come on.

1174
01:09:57.403 --> 01:09:59.613
Oh. no.
It's Dad.

1175
01:10:10.833 --> 01:10:12.126
How cute.

1176
01:10:12.334 --> 01:10:15.337
Little pollen pinchers
all in a row.

1177
01:10:17.798 --> 01:10:19.925
Prepare to attack. bees.

1178
01:10:21.760 --> 01:10:25.723
It'll take a miracle
to stop them now.

1179
01:10:29.059 --> 01:10:31.854
- Or a Gorgo.
- Gorgo?

1180
01:10:32.062 --> 01:10:35.399
Come on. You need to trust me.

1181
01:10:35.608 --> 01:10:38.068
Come on. guys!
What are you waiting for?

1182
01:10:42.531 --> 01:10:43.866
My dear bees.

1183
01:10:44.074 --> 01:10:47.161
remember our
dear departed Queen.

1184
01:10:47.369 --> 01:10:49.413
This is for her.

1185
01:10:49.622 --> 01:10:52.833
Today we make bee-story.

1186
01:10:53.042 --> 01:10:54.835
Enough fancy talk.

1187
01:10:55.044 --> 01:10:57.171
Spitball those syrup-suckers!

1188
01:11:02.134 --> 01:11:05.054
- Crawley... attack!
- Attack. Right.

1189
01:11:05.262 --> 01:11:07.681
First row. prepare buckets!

1190
01:11:07.890 --> 01:11:11.060
- I said attack. wax-brain!
- Oh. okay.

1191
01:11:11.268 --> 01:11:13.812
- Attack!
- But. Buzzlina...

1192
01:11:14.021 --> 01:11:17.691
- Do it now. you fool!
- Release the honey!

1193
01:11:17.900 --> 01:11:19.276
I said now!

1194
01:11:23.739 --> 01:11:26.825
Not on us. honey-heads!
The hornets!

1195
01:11:27.034 --> 01:11:28.702
Drop it on the hornets!

1196
01:11:30.412 --> 01:11:32.081
Charge!

1197
01:11:40.589 --> 01:11:41.924
Missed me!

1198
01:11:46.679 --> 01:11:50.182
- Get off. you fuzzy-buzzer!
- You get off.

1199
01:11:50.391 --> 01:11:52.977
you overgrown gnat!
Crawley!

1200
01:11:54.853 --> 01:11:57.564
Missed me! Too slow!
Who wants a piece of Crawley?

1201
01:12:09.576 --> 01:12:11.036
Gorgo.

1202
01:12:11.245 --> 01:12:16.208
Who wakes Gorge
from his sleep?

1203
01:12:19.753 --> 01:12:24.591
All this fighting
makes Gorgo hungry.

1204
01:12:28.637 --> 01:12:31.473
- Right! Go right!
- Left!

1205
01:12:31.682 --> 01:12:34.351
No. I said the other left!

1206
01:12:34.560 --> 01:12:39.523
Naughty bugs. the meadow
belongs to everyone!

1207
01:12:39.732 --> 01:12:44.653
Gorgo say: Bees
and hornets befriends.

1208
01:12:44.862 --> 01:12:46.113
And Gorgo say:

1209
01:12:46.322 --> 01:12:48.657
Give little bees pollen
whenever they're hungry.

1210
01:12:48.866 --> 01:12:51.702
- Willi!
- And let little hornets explore

1211
01:12:51.910 --> 01:12:53.287
wherever they want.

1212
01:12:53.495 --> 01:12:55.914
And how about some respect for
dung beetles while you're at it?

1213
01:13:00.127 --> 01:13:07.343
If bees and hornets want
to fight. they can fight Gorgo.

1214
01:13:07.551 --> 01:13:09.136
- Oh.
- Huh?

1215
01:13:10.554 --> 01:13:13.057
- Hi.
- She's with the hornets.

1216
01:13:13.265 --> 01:13:15.642
Buzzywump?
He's been bee-napped.

1217
01:13:15.851 --> 01:13:19.104
No. he hasn't!
Hornets and bees can befriends.

1218
01:13:19.313 --> 01:13:20.230
Look.

1219
01:13:21.648 --> 01:13:23.067
Friends?

1220
01:13:23.275 --> 01:13:25.903
Not friends. Dad.
Best friends.

1221
01:13:26.111 --> 01:13:29.531
- But what about our camp?
- It wasn't us.

1222
01:13:29.740 --> 01:13:32.618
Whoa. whoa. listen. listen.
We didn't do nothing.

1223
01:13:32.826 --> 01:13:35.913
Those flimsy hornet-huts.
they just fell over.

1224
01:13:38.582 --> 01:13:40.376
Enough with the
stupid ants.

1225
01:13:40.584 --> 01:13:42.878
Get those filthy jelly thieves.

1226
01:13:45.297 --> 01:13:46.673
Yes!

1227
01:13:47.966 --> 01:13:50.344
- Charge!
- Wait!

1228
01:13:50.552 --> 01:13:54.723
They didn't steal the jelly.
it was the Royal Adviser.

1229
01:13:54.932 --> 01:13:57.226
She's hiding it under her crown.

1230
01:13:59.269 --> 01:14:00.396
Oh. please!

1231
01:14:01.271 --> 01:14:03.399
Can you really trust a bee

1232
01:14:03.607 --> 01:14:05.818
who sneaks around in disguises

1233
01:14:06.026 --> 01:14:10.989
playing foolish
children's... games?

1234
01:14:24.044 --> 01:14:26.713
No! Dad!
No. please!

1235
01:14:26.922 --> 01:14:28.132
Dad. No!

1236
01:14:28.757 --> 01:14:31.552
Dad! Dad! Dad!

1237
01:14:31.760 --> 01:14:34.388
We can't save them
unless we work together!

1238
01:14:34.596 --> 01:14:37.683
Everybody.
grab a piece of Gorgo!

1239
01:14:49.778 --> 01:14:51.029
Lift!

1240
01:14:57.536 --> 01:14:59.163
It's working!

1241
01:15:07.463 --> 01:15:09.339
- Dad.
- Son.

1242
01:15:10.424 --> 01:15:13.302
- Dad.
- My little Buzzywump.

1243
01:15:14.761 --> 01:15:17.598
You're not going cry.
are you. Dad?

1244
01:15:17.806 --> 01:15:18.640
Me? Pah. no.

1245
01:15:18.849 --> 01:15:21.226
I just got something in my eye.

1246
01:15:21.435 --> 01:15:22.728
That's my Dad.

1247
01:15:22.936 --> 01:15:25.147
Crawley. my crown.

1248
01:15:27.524 --> 01:15:30.194
Look!
The royal jelly!

1249
01:15:33.489 --> 01:15:36.200
Thief!
Arrest him!

1250
01:15:37.159 --> 01:15:39.161
What are you waiting for?

1251
01:15:41.038 --> 01:15:43.999
Crawley. arrest
this hive traitor

1252
01:15:44.208 --> 01:15:45.918
or I'll have your stripes.

1253
01:15:47.419 --> 01:15:49.546
- Crawley? - Enough!

1254
01:15:49.755 --> 01:15:54.426
No more lies. Buzzlina.
You've caused enough hurt.

1255
01:15:54.635 --> 01:15:56.428
Are you disobeying me?

1256
01:15:56.637 --> 01:16:00.432
I am your Queen.
bow before me.

1257
01:16:00.641 --> 01:16:03.894
All of you
bow before your Queen.

1258
01:16:06.939 --> 01:16:09.274
<i>That's more like it. You...</i>

1259
01:16:09.483 --> 01:16:11.818
396. bow.

